title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the Cheddar cheese and hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake for another 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chicken burritos
directions: Combine soup and milk; set aside.
Combine chicken, broccoli and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Stir in 3/4 cup soup mixture.
Divide chicken mixture evenly between the tortillas and roll up.
Place, seam side down, on lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Stir tomato into remaining soup and pour over top of tortillas.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top of tortillas.
Cook for 5 more minutes.
Makes 6 Chicken Burritos.

title: chicken pie
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in pan.
Mix soups and broth together, heat and pour over chicken.

title: eggplant italian
directions: Peel and cut eggplant into pieces; cook until soft.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onion in olive oil until soft.
Add garlic and saute until just before browned.

title: "gen. creasy's favorite dish"
directions: Wash and pick clean.
Have water with meat boiling.
Add greens; salt to taste.
Cook until tender.
Serve with hot pepper.

title: chicken marsala (for one)
directions: In a saucepan, heat oil. Dredge chicken in flour and place in pan.
Cook until done, making sure not to burn chicken.
Add mushrooms. Deglaze pan with Marsala wine. Add beef stock; reduce by half. Slowly add half and half and cook for 1 minute.

title: carolina apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: all american barbecue
directions: Cook beef and onions in Dutch oven until tender, drain. Combine ketchup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Heat through.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half and remove yolks.
Mash & mix with the other ingredients and fill each egg.

title: sour cream pecan coffee cake
directions: Cream butter with
cup
of
sugar
until light.
Add eggs, 1 at a
time, beating well.
Add vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix flour,
baking
powder and soda.
Alternate blending flour mix and sour
cream
into	the
margarine mixture.
Mix well.
Combine in a
separate
bowl the rest of the sugar with the cinnamon and pecans.
Spread half of batter mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle
with
half of cinnamon nut mixture.
Top with the rest of the batter and spread out, then top with the rest of the cinnamon
mixture.	Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Drizzle melted
butter
or	squeeze butter over top during the last 5 minutes of baking.	(Could also be put into 2 smaller pans.)

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat egg yolks, shortening and margarine at high speed until well blended.
Gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add extracts and beat.

title: easy orange pound cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine
ingredients and mix. Pour into
a prepared tube pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Top with glaze while still warm.

title: mini fish pizzas
directions: Microwave fish fillets as directed on package.
Arrange muffin halves on microwavable plate or platter.
Place 1 hot fillet on each muffin half.
Mix tomato sauce and oregano.
Spoon over fish. Top with cheese.
Microwave, uncovered, until cheese begins to melt, 20 to 30 seconds.
Makes 4 pizzas.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Slice Twinkies lengthwise; place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Twinkies should cover the bottom of the dish.
Cover Twinkies with thawed strawberries.
Add layer of sliced bananas. Cover with instant vanilla pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.
Refrigerate one hour.
Serve immediately.

title: corn casserole
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pat's cheese bread
directions: Mix all together and spread on French or Italian bread.
Put under broiler until it sizzles.

title: spinach vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: chicken tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine muffin mix and cheese. Prepare according to package directions.
Set aside.
In saucepan, stir remaining ingredients until blended.
Heat through.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix Jell-O and Kool-Aid according to package directions.
Add pineapple juice.
Freeze in gallon plastic container.
When ready to serve, thaw several hours.
Put in punch bowl and pour Sprite or 7-Up over the frozen mix.

title: chive cheese balls(finger food)
directions: Divide the cream cheese into 30 equal pieces.
Separate biscuits and cut each into thirds.
Wrap a cube of cheese inside each piece of dough, forming a small ball.
Place the balls on a lightly greased cookie sheet and bake in a preheated 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: sherbet pineapple-orange
directions: Mix together.
Yields 1 gallon freezer ice cream sherbet.

title: asparagus-egg bake
directions: Wash and trim asparagus.
Cook in unsalted, boiling water until almost tender.
Drain the spears, reserving liquid.
Add 3 cups water to liquid and bring to a boil.
Stir in egg noodles and cook until limp but still slightly firm.
Drain well.

title: couscous porridge a la golden russets
directions: Heat the milk until just short of scalding, melting the butter in it, having added the salt already.
Dump in the couscous, then a generous handful of currants.
Remove from heat; stir it up, cover and let sit for five minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Cook milk, shortening and sugar until boiling, then set aside. When
lukewarm,
dissolve
yeast in it and sift enough flour in to make it the consistency of cake batter.
Let stand in warm place
for
hours,
then sift salt, soda and baking powder. Work in
enough
flour to make stiff dough, then roll out and cut as
many
rolls
as you wish.
Set in a warm place and let rise for 2 hours before baking.
Put the rest of dough in the icebox. Will keep a week or more.

title: pat in the pan pie crust
directions: Place all ingredients in pie pan and mix with hands until mixture forms a soft dough.
Press firmly and evenly against bottom and sides of pie pan (not on the rim).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Cool and fill with any cream filling.

title: italian ricotta pie(traditional easter dessert)
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar and eggs.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add to cheese mixture.
Pour into pie crust shell (thick). Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: joyce's chinese cabbage
directions: Shred as much cabbage as you want to eat at a meal.
Chop or dice your celery, carrots and apples according to how much you want in proportion to your cabbage.

title: banana cream trifle
directions: In a large mixing bowl prepare pudding mix as directed on pkg. using two cups of milk.
Layer half of the bread cubes, pudding mix, banana slices and whipped topping in a 2 quart serving bowl.
Repeat with remaining ingredients; then cover and refrigerate.

title: golden nuggets
directions: Cream butter and 1 1/4 cups sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour, salt and cinnamon and add to creamed mixture.
Shape into small balls.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and roll balls in the mixture.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Press walnut halves on each and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: california blend casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, mushroom soup and approximately 3/4 can of onions together. Put half of mixture in baking pan.
Lay slices of cheese on top.
Cover with remaining mixture of vegetables.
Cover with cheese.
Add rest of onions on top when approximately 15 minutes of cooking time left.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tator candy
directions: Boil tator until done.
Peel while hot.
Mash until lumps are gone.
Add vanilla and sugar using about 1 cup sugar at a time. Add milk when mixture becomes stiff.
Roll out on sugar.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll into a loaf.
Chill for 5 minutes. Slice in quarters and dip in powdered sugar.

title: fiesta potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender, then drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat berry bavarian
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice cubes to make 2 cups.
Add gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Spoon into 8 dessert dishes.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm.
Garnish with whipped topping and raspberries.

title: tropical apple slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mayonnaise; mix well.
Add mayonnaise; toss until all ingredients are well coated.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well until smooth and creamy. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving in covered container.

title: scotch oatcakes
directions: In bowl mix all ingredients except milk.
Once mixed, blend in milk.
Mix well.
Divide the dough into 6 parts.
Roll each part into a five inch circle.
Cut each circle into quarters (pie slice sections).
Bake at 450° on a greased pan for 15 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, lemon and almond flavorings.
Sift flour 3 times, then add alternately with milk, starting and ending with flour.
With last bit of flour, add baking powder.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Turn oven on after putting in cake.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix well all of the ingredients, except nuts and cranberries. Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Bake at 350° in 1 big loaf pan or 2 small pans.

title: zucchini squares
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, oil, oatmeal, baking soda, salt, baking powder, flour, eggs, zucchini and vanilla.
Fold in nuts. Spoon onto a well-greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Let cool.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Bring celery, onion and broccoli to boil.
Cook 5 minutes and drain.
Add rice, butter and soup.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole; spread Cheez Whiz over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mistakes
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Drain.
Melt cheese in skillet with sausage.
Mix in garlic and Worcestershire.
Remove from heat.
Arrange bread on cookie sheet in a single layer.
Put about one tablespoon of sausage mixture on each piece of bread. Bake in oven at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix
dressing mix and melted margarine together. Spread half of	mixture
in
a	small casserole dish (greased).
Fold remaining ingredients together and put on top of dressing. Use the other
half
of
dressing
on top.	Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fabulous cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large bowl with electric mixer at high speed, beat cream cheese with cottage cheese until creamy and well combined.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream the margarine or butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients with the evaporated milk and vanilla.

title: diet oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Spread oats and nuts on ungreased cookie sheet and toast 5 to 7 minutes and set aside.
Simmer raisins in 1/2 cup water until plump and drain. In mixer, beat sugar, apple butter, egg, oil and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mix, oats, nuts and raisins. Drop on greased sheets about 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes about 40 medium size cookies. Calories, 114, fat 3g, sodium 46 mg, cho 9 mg.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown the pork in the soy sauce.
Add the celery and onion. Add the mushroom soup, mushrooms, bean sprouts and noodles.
Put into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pork is done.
During the last 10 minutes of baking, sprinkle chow mein noodles on top.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Day before serving:
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, heat to boiling all ingredients except mushrooms; cover and simmer over low heat 10 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms until coated.
Cook over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes or until fork tender.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: black bean soup(with secret ingredient)
directions: In a large soup pot, heat oil. Add onions and cook over medium heat until lightly brown. Add garlic, cumin, cinnamon and cayenne pepper. Cook for 1 minute. Add all remaining ingredients except cheese. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until ready to serve. Add extra chicken broth if it gets too thick.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and salt until mixture is lemon-colored.
Add butter and flour and blend well.
Add milk and fold in 1 cup coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with remaining coconut.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: oven fried vegetables(a weight watcher recipe)
directions: Put vegetables in a bowl and toss with oil.
Arrange in a shallow layer on a nonstick cookie sheet; sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes at 425°.

title: riley's homemade bailey's
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; mix well.
Can be stored up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: sausage italian
directions: Brown sausage in a large frying pan.
When sausage is cooked, cut into 1-inch pieces.
Put remaining ingredients into crock-pot; add sausage.
Cook on high 1 hour.
Cook on low 7 to 8 hours. Serve over spaghetti.

title: anasazi veggies
directions: In white wine saute onions and peppers.
Add other ingredients, sauteing over medium heat until squash is tender.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Put sausage in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cubed bread.
Beat eggs and pour over the top.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Pour milk over it.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form into ball and cover with chopped pecans.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and save broth. Mix all ingredients in a large pan and top with shredded cheese. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: glen's soup
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add sausage and brown some more.
Add water, tomato sauce, tomatoes, Veg-All, beans and starter mix. Cook in large pot on high for 15 to 20 minutes, then let simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
The best soup in Ware County!

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: In a saucepan add cocoa, sugar, butter and milk together. Bring to a rolling boil, about 3 minutes. Keep ingredients stirred. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oatmeal. Mix together. Spoon or drop onto wax paper.

title: sherry icebox cake
directions: Line a medium size spring-form pan with ladyfinger halves. Combine egg yolks and sugar.
Beat cream until stiff.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Soak gelatin in cold water; dissolve in hot water and combine with egg yolk mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and egg whites.
Add flavoring; pour into ladyfinger lined pan and chill until firm.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix ingredients together and press into greased or Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream brown sugar, margarine and white sugar together.

Blend in egg, 1/3 cup peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla. Stir in flour and oats. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with package of chocolate chips. Let stand until melted, then smooth over top. Combine powdered sugar, 1/4 cup peanut butter and milk. Drizzle over top. Cool. Cut into bars.

title: potato soup
directions: Simmer on medium-low heat, water, hash brown potatoes, broth, celery and onion.
Add chicken soup, milk and celery soup. Melt in Velveeta cheese.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Chop meat into 1/2-inch cubes and brown in small amount of oil.
Drain when done.
Cook celery and onions in small amount of water until soft; drain.
Add the cooked vegetables to the prepared meat; also add the soy sauce, rice (uncooked), chicken and rice soup and cream of mushroom soup; mix together and place in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Remember to stir a few times while cooking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, beginning with your dry ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan or loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Put into a bowl and stir in, slowly, butter and broth.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into a pan of boiling salted chicken broth.
Cover the pan and let boil slowly for about ten or fifteen minutes.
Drop in boned chicken and simmer.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popcorn, pecans and peanuts before you melt marshmallows. Melt oil, oleo and marshmallows.
Drizzle over popcorn, pecans and peanuts.
Put in M&M's last.
Butter hands good.
Spray pans with Pam.
Make cakes and make sure mixture is firm before removing from pan.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Combine all ingredients (do not brown ground beef), adding water one can at a time.
Cook slowly, about 1 1/2 hours.
You can use a crock-pot.

title: banana oat muffins
directions: Combine butter, eggs, bananas and honey; mix until smooth. Mix together yogurt and baking soda; add to banana mixture.
Cream well, then add flour, bran, wheat germ and oats and stir until just blended.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: italian pork noodles
directions: Cut boneless pork; stir-fry in 1/2 teaspoon vegetable oil, onion and mushrooms.
Stir in tomatoes and Italian seasoning. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked noodles. Serves 4.

title: minestrone soup
directions: *Can use an equal amount of reconstituted beef bouillon.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 1 unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduced to 350° and cook until set in center.
Cover with meringue, if wanted.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Crumble six cups Doritos with your hands into a large mixing bowl.
Add onion, chili, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, and 1 1/2 cup cheddar cheese to the Doritos. Stir with a rubber spatula to combine.
Place mixture in a 8 1/2x11 oven proof casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat egg and add the milk.
Add egg and milk mixture to sifted dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Holding your finger over the bottom of funnel, pour some batter into it.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Garlic salt may be substituted for regular salt if desired.

title: hearty tomato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples, cut in eighths and arrange in a 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Sift remaining 1/2 cup sugar with flour.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Then in moderate oven (350°) for about 40 minutes, until apples are tender.

title: lemon tarts
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan; stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until thick.
Cool.
Fold in sour cream.
Chill.
Serve in pastry shells.
Serves 6 to 8 dessert-size shells.
More in smaller shells.

title: caramel dip
directions: Heat and stir all ingredients in microwave until smooth and warm.
Pour over apple slices or dip apples into mixture.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fudge
directions: Put into a large bowl chocolate chips, butter and vanilla. Put into a large saucepan (thick bottomed) sugar and milk.
Bring to boil and boil exactly 6 minutes from start of boil over medium heat.
Remove from stove and pour over ingredients in bowl and stir until butter and chips are melted and mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into lightly greased pan; let stand for 6 hours and cut into squares.
Top with nuts, if desired.

title: e-z company chicken
directions: Trim fat off chicken.
Place chicken in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Mix oleo, sour cream and can of creamy chicken mushroom soup together until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with onions (Durkee) as much as you desire.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta fruit salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and rinse well in cold water. Place in a large bowl. Add the fruit. Combine yogurt and orange juice concentrate. Pour over salad and toss to coat. Cover and chill for several hours. Yield: 10 servings.

title: pickled beets
directions: Make enough liquid from sugar, cider vinegar and water until all jars of beets have been filled to very top and sealed.
Wash beets.
Trim off tops and roots.
Place in large pot and cover with water.
Cover pot and bring water to boil.
Continue to cook beets until just fork-tender to center.
Pour off hot water and add cold to cover.
Change cold water until beets have cooled.
If beets overcook, pickles will be mushy!
Skin and slice cooked beets.
Loosely fill sterile jars.
Put 2 cloves in each jar. Boil together sugar, vinegar and water 5 minutes.
Fill each jar with liquid; seal and process on rack covered with boiling water for 5 minutes.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bowl, add all ingredients. Stir until potatoes are evenly coated.
Place potatoes into a shallow baking pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: corn and hominy surprise
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in casserole dish at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: creamed cabbage slaw
directions: Chop cabbage fine and mix with other ingredients.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water until dissolved. Stir in orange juice and oranges. Mix well and let congeal. Mix pudding and milk. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread over congealed jello. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fudge icing
directions: Bring to full boil; boil 1 minute.
Cool and beat in cold water until firm.
Frost cake.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Pack in jars and seal. Serve with fish.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients (except muffin mix) well.
Add muffin mix.
Stir.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Cut up chicken breasts and cook for about 10 minutes until almost done. Mix Stove Top Stuffing according to box recipe. Place stuffing in large casserole dish. Place chicken on top of stuffing. Heat soup as directed on can., then pour over chicken and stuffing. Place in oven at 400 degrees for at least 25 to 30 minutes.

title: can do chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 round pans or 1 oblong pan.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat on low speed 30 minutes, scraping sides and bottom of bowl.
Beat 3 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add bananas and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cube chicken and put in a casserole with chopped celery, uncooked rice and the seasonings.
Add the liquid which may be either milk or gravy and water.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth along with 1 cup water.
Melt 1 stick oleo in skillet and brown celery and onions.
Mix flour, milk, cheese, soup and 1 cup chicken broth.
Drain spaghetti when cooked and combine with sauce in pan.
Add chicken and mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger-onion pie
directions: Mix Bisquick and cream well.
Knead 10 times on floured board. Roll dough in a circle to fit a 9-inch pie pan.
Saute beef and onions until brown.
Add seasonings and Bisquick.
Pour into dough-lined pan.
Beat eggs and blend with cottage cheese.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: canned salsa
directions: Combine tomatoes, peppers, onion, salt, garlic and vinegar in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes.
Pour into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps and process in boiling water bath for 30 minutes. Makes about 6 half pints.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.
Shape into balls; bake on cookie sheet at
for 15 minutes if not frozen, but if frozen 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: To make frosting, place first 5 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil 1 minute. Set aside to cool. Mix vanilla pudding with milk. Stir in Cool Whip.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine evaporated milk, margarine, maple syrup and caramels. Cook slowly over low heat until melted and smooth, stirring often. Add vanilla; stir and pour over popcorn and peanuts.
Mix well.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Lightly grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Place about 2-inches apart in pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown. Remove immediately from pan. Serve pan. Yield: about 7 dozen appetizers.

title: marcene's whole wheat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder into bowl.
Combine eggs, milk and melted butter. Stir into dry ingredients.
Grease muffin tin and fill 2/3 full with mixture.

title: broccoli supreme garden vegetables
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients in butter (leave a little crunchy).
Prepare
Rice-A-Roni
as
directed.
Mix
together. Real good with fried, roasted or baked chicken.

title: lemon sherry chicken
directions: Season chicken, then flatten using meat mallet or rolling pin. Melt butter in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken. Cook until brown, about 5 minutes. Add sherry and lemon juice. Bring to a boil.
Turn.
Add lemon peel.
Place on plate.
Pour juice over chicken, then top with Parmesan cheese.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers along bottom of pan.
Heat margarine, sugar and egg in saucepan until melted.
Pour over vanilla wafers. Put strawberries on top of this, then top with Cool Whip.
(May sprinkle with chopped pecans.)

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, reserving about 1 cup of shredded cheese to scatter on top.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° until done, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mom's christmas pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour, pecans, cherries and pineapple.
Mix well.
Add lemon extract and blend well.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown the meat with the onion and garlic until meat is cooked through.
Drain any fat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir. Heat but do not boil.
Serve over noodles.

title: cranberry molded salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sour cream and cranberry sauce until well mixed.
Mold and chill.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Place artichoke hearts in chopping bowl.
Chop into small pieces.
Combine artichokes and all other ingredients in large bowl.
Mix together.
Reserve 1/2 of chopped pimentos for the top. Transfer to casserole and smooth out top.
Refrigerate until 40 minutes prior to serving.
(This can be done up to 1 day ahead.)

title: cereal crunch cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, margarine and oil.
Add eggs, then remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes until lightly browned.

title: barley soup
directions: Brown meat in oil. Add water or stock and bring to a boil. Skim off foam if present. Add parsley and spices; cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add barley and vegetables; cover and simmer an hour or until barley is done. Add Tamari sauce and garnish with chopped fresh parsley.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sift flour with sugar, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add apples, nuts, margarine and eggs.
Beat until just combined (it will be thick).
Turn into pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until top springs back when lightly pressed with fingertip.
Serve warm. Top with whipped cream.

title: pinata
directions: Will also need 1 (9-inch) round balloon and a newspaper.

title: randy's smoked turkey
directions: Thaw
turkey
in
refrigerator.
Boil 2 quarts of water and add
brown	sugar
and Tender Quick.
Mix well.
Pump this into turkey
with
a
cooking
syringe.	Leave in brine in the refrigerator
for 3 days before cooking.
Then cover with foil or use a
cooking bag and bake in oven or smoker at 325° until thermometer reaches 180° to 185°.

title: fat ladies
directions: Mix cake with melted butter and 1/3 cup canned milk. Spread 1/2 of mix in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 325° for 6 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips. Melt caramels with remaining milk (1/3 cup). Pour over nuts and chocolate chips. Spread remaining cake mixture over the top. Bake about 15 to 20 minutes more. Cool and slice in small pieces.

title: twelve layer chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and add alternately with milk and oil.
Cook layers in oven on highest temperature (not broil), using an iron griddle.
Use 1/2 cup of batter per layer.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.	Stir in soup.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat.	Serve over noodles.

title: tuna stroganoff
directions: Dip dove breasts in soy sauce.
Wrap with 1/2 slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick if necessary. Place on grill or in the oven (350°) on a rack in a pan.
Cook for approximately 30 minutes or until the breast is tender.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Put cake pieces into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Drizzle jello over top.
Let set for a few minutes in refrigerator.
Pour prepared pudding over this and add slices of banana over top.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: great gazpacho
directions: Dice onion, tomatoes, green pepper and cucumber.
Combine all ingredients and chill for 2 hours. Top with chopped scallions. You may puree the soup, if desired.
Serves 6 people.

title: skillet scramble
directions: In a large skillet, saute the potatoes, green pepper and onion in oil.
Sprinkle with onion powder, garlic powder and seasoned salt; mix well.
In a bowl, combine the eggs, ham, water, salsa, salt and pepper.
Add to the potato mixture,
Cook until the eggs are set.
Sprinkle with cheese; cook 2 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6-8.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain noodles.
Rinse with cold water.
Mix Ricotta, egg, parsley and 1 cup Mozzarella in a bowl; set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese together.
Pour in corn and chilies.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Mix. Bake in muffin pan at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 good size rolls.

title: crunchy tuna pockets
directions: Rinse tuna in colander 1 minute; let drain 1 minute.
Combine tuna with next 5 ingredients and toss gently.
Combine mayo, lemon juice and dill.
Toss gently with other combined ingredients. Cover and chill for 1 hour or until serving.
When ready to serve, spoon into halved pita pockets.
Use celery leaves to garnish. Makes 6 servings.
Great for picnics, summertime entertaining or lunch anytime!

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Stir in 1/4 cup flour.
Add chicken broth, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Lower heat and add cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken, carrots and the pimento.
Spread in shallow 2-quart casserole.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Add seasoned stuffing mix and mix well.
Spread over chicken mixture. Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken in salt water; cool and debone.
Take 1 1/2 quarts broth from chicken and boil vermicelli in it.
Do not drain.
Saute bell pepper, celery and onion in margarine; add this to vermicelli along with Ro-Tel tomatoes, chicken and cheese. Heat until cheese is melted.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° until bubbly.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, oil, milk and eggs and beat until well blended.
Put in 1/2 package frozen strawberries, 1/2 cup pecans and 1/2 cup coconut.
Bake in three greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool cake on wire racks.

title: microwave nachos
directions: Place paper towel on a microwave-safe plate.
Arrange tortilla chips on Bounty-lined plate.
Sprinkle with cheese, olives and pepper.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 2 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts, rotating plate once or twice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: herb-roasted potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in bite-size chunks.
Place oil and soup mix in a large Ziploc bag.
Add potatoes and mix well till all covered.
Pour potatoes into a baking dish sprayed with pan spray.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Stirring every 15 minutes.

title: brie almondine
directions: Saute almonds in butter until just toasted.
Place Brie with rind in small ovenproof serving dish.
Pour almond mixture over cheese.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 7 minutes, until cheese starts to melt.
Serve immediately with crackers.

title: porcupine meatballs in chili sauce
directions: Combine ground chuck, rice, onion and bell pepper.
Form into small to medium balls.
In large saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Bring chili sauce to boil over medium heat.
Add meatballs.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Reduce to simmer for 20 minutes. May be served over hot rice.

title: black forest seasoning salt
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: seven bean bake
directions: Saute pork, celery and onion.
Mix all ingredients together in roaster pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken sandwich deluxe
directions: In a medium bowl, place chicken.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and let set for 5 minutes.

title: chicken nacho dip
directions: Reserve 1 teaspoon taco seasoning mix; set aside.
Combine remaining taco seasoning mix, chicken, beer and chiles in a large skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until mixture is thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in salsa.

title: cole porter's three fruit cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine all of the ingredients except the mayonnaise.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, stir in the mayonnaise.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add nuts and mix.
Combine slightly beaten eggs with remaining ingredients.
Pour all at once into dry ingredients.
Blend lightly.
Bake in 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poverty sop
directions: Brown the flour with the bacon drippings until brown and thick.
Add the salt and pepper.
Mix well and add milk, cooking and stirring until desired thickness.
Sop with biscuits.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix oleo, flour and pecans.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Combine sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup topping.
Mix pudding and cold milk; spread over cream cheese mixture in pan.
Spread rest of whipped topping over mixture and refrigerate.

title: bloody mary mix
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Add vodka to mix or serve as Virgin Mary.
Adjust spices to your own taste.

title: grandma ferry's dumplings for snitz and knepp
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in fat; add milk.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of the stew.
Cook, uncovered, for about 5 minutes.
Now cover and cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Do not uncover until they have steamed 15 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in large oblong pan the refried beans, ground beef cooked in taco seasoning mix, green chiles, black olives, cheese and taco sauce.
Bake for 20 minutes in oven at 425°.
Stir in one cup of sour cream.
Serve with Doritos or nachos.

title: cinnamon raisin biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples in cider until tender.
Press through a sieve or food mill; measure 3 quarts of apple pulp.
Cook pulp until thick enough to round up in a spoon.
As pulp thickens, stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Add sugar and spices.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently until thick, about 1 hour.
Pour hot, into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process pints and quarts for 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring cocoa, milk and margarine to good boil.
Remove from heat and beat in powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts, if desired.

title: chocolate mint patties
directions: Mix all ingredients until stiff.
Form into patties.
Dip in chocolate; place on wax paper to set.

title: oyster casserole or dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach and set aside.
Melt butter; add all spices.
Drain oysters and blot with towel.
Combine butter mixture with drained spinach.
Add bread crumbs and oysters and stir gently.
Place in a greased casserole and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then uncover for 15 minutes.
Serve with Melba toast for appetizer.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square baking pan with foil.
Combine sugar, Marshmallow Creme, milk, butter, Kahlua and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to rapid boil, stirring constantly for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add all chocolate.
Stir until melted.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Turn into pan.
Refrigerate until firm (overnight).
Cut into squares.
Keep in refrigerator until desired use.

title: marge birsky's hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients (tomatoes, undrained) in saucepan.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat, then simmer, covered, for 1 hour, until vegetables are tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper; remove bay leaf.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain liquid from salmon and remove skin and bones.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add cream cheese.
Chill overnight. Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts and parsley.

title: fast fixin' chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan.
Stir with fork or spoon until blended (about 2 minutes).
Scrape sides and spread evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Use a knife to loosen cake from sides.
Cut and serve directly from pan.
Store leftover cake loosely covered.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and beat 2 minutes.
Fold in the chocolate chips.
Bake in well greased and floured bunt pan for 50-55 minutes at 350 degrees.
Let cool in pan about 20-25 minutes.

title: no cholesterol egg
directions: Beat in blender.
Keeps
in
refrigerator
for	up to 1 week; 3 to 4 tablespoons equals one egg.

title: gourmet veal burger
directions: In large frying pan, saute butter, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Broil ground veal steaks until brown on both sides. Serve on a toasted bun topped with the sauteed mixture.
Season to taste.

title: peanut brittle(microwave oven method)
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole or microwave-safe container.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Stop and stir well.
Return to oven and microwave on High 4 minutes more.
Stop.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa. Put all ingredients in saucepan and cook over medium heat until margarine is melted.
Bake in uncooked pie shell for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: feather sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add water and continue beating until very thick.
Gradually add sugar and extract.
Sift flour with salt 3 times.
Fold in egg yolk mixture a little at a time.
Beat egg whites until foamy and then add cream of tartar.
Beat until real moist and glossy looking.
Fold this into first mixture.
Bake in ungreased pan at 325° for 1 hour. Remove from oven, invert pan and completely cool before removing from the pan. cut into 3 layers and fill with the filling.

title: zucchini paisano
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Cook zucchini and mushrooms in oil until zucchini is tender-crisp, about 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in tomato sauce, seasonings and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Boil milk and flour by adding the flour gradually until thickened.
Let cool about 5 minutes.
Beat in sugar and Crisco.

title: tangier island corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: tapioca jello
directions: Cook tapioca according to directions on box.
Do not use milk. Use the juice from the oranges and pineapple. Then enough water to equal 3 cups.
Cool.

title: lil's meat loaf and sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and form into loaf.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and oranges. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish or larger.
Put in refrigerator until set.
Mix sour cream with mayonnaise and spread over congealed Jell-O mixture.
Sprinkle marshmallows and cheese on top of mayonnaise and sour cream mixture.
Keeps a week in refrigerator.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1/2 gallon container.
Pour into 2 sterilized wine bottles.
Cover, cork and store in a cool dry place for 30 days.
Serve as you like.
Makes approximately 1/2 gallon of Kahlua (coffee brandy).

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, then add milk.
Pour into pie crust and cook on 450° for 25 minutes or until done.
I do not use flavoring, you can add some if you like.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and place in tortilla.
Roll up and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour sauce over and add more shredded cheese on top.
Serve with gucamole, sour cream and picante sauce.

title: skewered grilled potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and water in a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole; cover.
Microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until tender, stirring after 8 minutes.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients until well blended.
Stir in potatoes.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Arrange potatoes on skewers.
Place on grill over hot coals.
Grill, covered, 6 to 8 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown, brushing occasionally with reserved marinade and turning after 4 minutes.
(Spraying the grill rack with nonstick cooking spray helps keep potatoes from sticking.)

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cover bottom of dish with Tater Tots and cook on 350° for 10 minutes.
In a skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain fat and add broccoli and steam.
Put on top of Tater Tots.
Mix in a bowl together soup, milk, 3/4 of cheese and 1/2 can of onion rings. Cook for 25 minutes.
Top with rest of cheese and onion rings. Stick back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: judy's lemon cake
directions: Mix as directed on the box, adding extra egg and oil.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 rounds.

title: no-sugar banana bread
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in 2 eggs and apple juice concentrate.
Add bananas.
Mix flour, salt, soda and wheat germ; add to banana mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green jacket salad
directions: The dressing will look very thick, but it covers a whole salad.
The salad is best when served ice cold.
Croutons or baked pieces of pita bread are good with it.

title: potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: meat loaf italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, cracker crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, 1 cup of cheese, oregano, basil, garlic, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Mix well and add meat.
Mix thoroughly and shape into flat rectangle about 10 x 12 inches on waxed paper.
Sprinkle remaining 2 cups cheese over meat.
Roll like a jelly roll and press ends together to seal.
Place on rack in shallow baking dish.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain off fat.
Pour on remaining tomato sauce and bake 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.

title: chicken dish
directions: Put all together.
Mix well.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix soda and flour. Set aside. Cream the butter and sugar slowly. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Stir in sour cream. Add vanilla. Add flour, one cup at a time, mixing well.
Use tube pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool. Take a knife and loosen sides.
Cool on rack.

title: carrot bread
directions: Cream the sugar, oil, salt and cinnamon. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add the cooked carrots and nuts. Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: dallas cowboy tacos
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until well browned; drain.
Stir in the onions and also brown.
When completed, open can of rolls and stretch the dough until thin, without splitting or tearing.

title: ranch dressing mix plus
directions: Combine first eight ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container in a cool dry place.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Make into thick patties and brown in skillet.
Combine mushroom soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: lentil soup with spinach
directions: Cook and stir onions and garlic in oil in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until onions are tender.
Stir in water, lentils and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Stir in spinach, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cover and simmer until spinach is tender, about 5 minutes.

title: yogurt dinner rolls(low calorie)
directions: In a bowl, combine water, sugar and yeast.
Set aside for about 5 minutes, or until bubbly; then add yogurt, margarine, egg, herbs and onion.
Set aside.

title: gwen's enchiladas
directions: Make meat filling ahead of time by frying together ground beef, onion, salt and pepper and chili. Add water for sauce.

title: shrimp creole
directions: *Always buy the best fresh shrimp.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 35 minutes.
Makes own crust.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In electric skillet, combine ring bologna (chopped bite size), kidney beans (don't drain) and stewed tomatoes (don't drain). Boil rice.
Add to mixture. Add chili powder; salt to taste. Simmer on low about 20 minutes.

title: aunt jennie's butter cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream butter until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in egg, milk and vanilla.
Add baking powder and salt, mixing well.
Gradually blend in flour, mixing thoroughly.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Boil raisins in water until tender.
Drain liquid from raisins.
Combine sugar, flour and salt and gradually stir in milk.
Add raisins.
Cook and stir over hot water for 5 minutes. Add beaten egg yolks and cook until thick.
Pour into baked shell. Cover with meringue.

title: chicken with pineapple glaze
directions: Mix this all together well and brush over chicken. Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a ball. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: egg breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread on one side and dice into 1/2-inch cubes.
Grate cheese.
In 2-quart buttered casserole, alternate layers of bread and cheese (4 layers).
Mix rest of ingredients.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Take an unbleached muslin bag, put some sweet fresh hay in bottom of the bag; add the ham and put hay firmly all around ham. Tie the bag and hang in dry place.
Ham treated in this manner will keep for years.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: Grease two 9-inch round layer cake pans.
Line with wax paper extending up sides of pans; grease wax paper.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt oleo; add mixed dry ingredients.
Combine eggs and vanilla and add to dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased pie pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Two bunches means 2 clusters as it is purchased.

title: the ultimate sugar cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar and Crisco in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, syrup and vanilla.
Beat well. Combine 3 cups flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture at low speed. Mix until well blended.
Divide dough into quarters.
If dough is too sticky, refrigerate 1 hour.
Keep covered until ready to roll. Place a quarter roll of dough on floured paper.
Roll dough to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut out with floured cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Sprinkle with sugar or decors if desired. Bake at 375° for 5 to 9 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and spread on flour tortillas.
Roll tightly and chill.

title: sour cream cranberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter and flour two 7 x 5-inch loaf pans. In medium bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. In large bowl, with electric mixer, beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar and orange peel; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream and orange juice alternately with flour mixture.
Blend in fresh cranberries.
Pour into prepared pans and bake for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: hot crab dip
directions: *Low-fat cream cheese and reduced fat mayo may be used, results are delicious.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In blender or food processor, process oats until coarse flour.
In a small bowl combine ground oats, flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine margarine and cream cheese in microwave oven until soft. Combine with spinach, artichokes, black pepper and 1 teaspoon lemon juice. Stir well. Spoon into a lightly greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: In saucepan, combine cider, spices and lemon juice. Cover and heat over medium-low heat for 30 minutes. Strain.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: mini pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Add cheese to meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on party rye bread.
Place in 350° to 375° oven about 10 minutes, if not frozen.
May be frozen first and baked as needed.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Put chicken in bottom of oblong casserole dish.
Tear tortillas in pieces and place on top of chicken.
Melt butter in saucepan; add onion and cook until tender.
Add soup and tomatoes and let come to a boil.
Pour over chicken and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili egg puff
directions: In bowl of electric mixer, beat eggs until light and lemony. Add flour, baking powder, cottage cheese, Jack cheese and melted butter.
Blend smooth, then stir in chilies.
Pour mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until top is browned and center appears firm.

title: cherry-coconut bars
directions: Measure flour; mix with butter and powdered sugar until smooth.
Spread this with fingers in ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake for 25 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Mix liquids and butter; add potatoes and onions and cook until done. Mix cracker crumbs, flour and seasonings. Add to potato and onions mixture. Add red and green peppers after you have chopped and sauteed briefly in butter; mix well. Bring to a boil; add cream (or milk) and corn. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. This makes 2 or more quarts.

title: jersey baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Place chicken in ungreased baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with white or brown rice, salad and cranberry sauce.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Beat eggs until light. Add mashed bananas and lemon juice; blend with shortening and sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; mix quickly into banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 375° for 90 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon and remove bones, if any.
Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Fry on both sides until golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter together.
Add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Add well beaten egg to creamed mixture. Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together and add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough well, then form into balls the size of a walnut.
Place balls on lightly greased baking sheet. Flatten with fork dipped in flour, making a crisscross pattern. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook together milk, sugar and 2 tablespoons butter until it comes to a soft ball stage. Then add peanut butter and 1 tablespoon butter. Stir together and pour into buttered platter.

title: chili chip casserole
directions: Spread broken tortilla chips in bottom of casserole dish. Pour chili over chips.
Top with cheese, onion, olives and/or peppers.
Bake until warmed through.
Serve with sour cream and lettuce.

title: pork chops and vegetables
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add chops, 3 at a time; brown well on both sides.
Remove and set aside.
Add green peppers and onions; saute for 3 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Stir in flour; cook and stir for 1 minute.
Blend in onion soup, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and salt.
Bring to boiling point.
Return chops to skillet; spoon sauce over chops.
Cover and simmer until tender abut 1 hour.
Stir in tomatoes, sauteed green peppers and onions.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Rub seasoned salt into roast.
Brown lightly.
Add water; cover and simmer until tender (2 to 2 1/2 hours).
Remove meat from juice to cool.
Measure 2 cups meat juice.
Add tomato sauce and beef stew mix.
Add brown sugar.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Shred meat and add to sauce.
Makes delicious sandwiches.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pothead pot roast
directions: Salt and pepper pot roast; brown on all sides in 1 tablespoon oil.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and pour over roast.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: green tomato sweet pickles
directions: Soak tomato slices in mixture of lime and water for 24 hours. Remove tomatoes from lime water and soak in clear water for 4 hours, changing water each hour.
Remove from water.
Mix sugar, vinegar and allspice (tied in gauze cloth loosely).
Put tomato slices and sugar mixture together and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and let stand 24 hours in solution.
Cook gently 1 hour, then seal in hot jars.

title: cream scones
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut margarine into flour, sugar, baking powder and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in 1 egg, the currants, orange rind and just enough half and half so dough leaves side of bowl.	Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead lightly ten times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.

title: german potato salad
directions: Scrub and cut up new potatoes, with skins on.
Cook until tender; drain well.
While potatoes are still hot, add Ranch dressing.
Put in serving dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: v-8 juice hot
directions: In a hurry?
Serve V-8 hot for appetizer.
Add small can spicy V-8 for a little spice.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
The thinner the batter, the lighter the hush puppies.
Drop into hot grease and brown both sides.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients for a fantastic barbecue sauce.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Mix together and place in pie crust.
Freeze.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook pie shell as directed; set aside.
In skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain excess oil off.
Add onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Place in cooked pie shell.
Cover with American cheese. Place in oven at 150° until cheese has melted.

title: chess pie bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Put in bottom of 8 x 8 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Mix brown sugar, 1/2 cup sugar and flour. Add to beaten eggs. Add melted butter and vanilla; mix well. Pour over baked pastry. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 60 minute hot rolls
directions: Heat margarine, milk and water to lukewarm.
Add sugar, salt and yeast.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour until dough is no longer sticky.
Let stand until dough has doubled in bulk.
Press down; knead and roll into small balls.
Let the dough rise again and bake at 400°.

title: chicken monte carlo
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Mix together other ingredients (soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese).
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with Pepperidge Farm mix and melted margarine.
Return to oven and brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease shallow 1 1/2-quart or 8-inch square baking dish.
Set aside.

title: graham cracker toffee
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with aluminum foil, dull side up. Spray with Pam.
Break crackers into small sections at the perforations.
Lay crackers close together (within 1/8 to 1/4-inch).
In a medium saucepan, bring the margarine, sugar and flavoring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly for 2 minutes. Pour mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove immediately and sprinkle with chocolate chips, if desired.
Cool on wire rack.
Break into sections; store in refrigerator.

title: sweet fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom and sides of 12-cup fluted tube pan or 10-inch tube pan.
In large bowl, combine eggs and water.
Add remaining ingredients by hand.
Stir until combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 30 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Brown meatballs and add to sauce.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Layer these in large bowl.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours, mixing occasionally.
Meanwhile, mix vinegar and sugar until sugar is dissolved; pour over drained cucumbers.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: hidden cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
With electric mixer, beat cream cheese, sugar, egg and salt; set aside.
Fill cupcake liners 3/4 full.
Drop teaspoon of cheese mixture to which chocolate chips have been added, into each cupcake-filled liner. Bake according to directions on cake mix package.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in casserole dish. Combine all ingredients in dish with melted margarine.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool for 5 minutes before serving.

title: spanish coffee
directions: Use red wine glasses with a large bowl.
Heat water in glasses in microwave.
Make one drink a a time.
Place the Cointreau and sugar in the glass and swirl, then flame, caramelizing the sugar. Add coffee.
Add rest of liquor.
Top with whipped cream, sugar and chocolate jimmies.
Makes 1.
Turn off the lights when flaming; a great show and a great drink!

title: tuna cheese twist
directions: Mix baking mix and 1/2 cup water until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth into ball on floured cloth. Knead 5 times.
Roll into 14 x 11-inch rectangle.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: grandma's original homemade potato pancakes
directions: Pour oil 3/4 inch in deep frying pan.
Grate potatoes in wooden bowl.
Add salt, pepper, egg and cinnamon.
Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes and applesauce.
Add corn flake crumbs, a little at a time, until slightly firm.
Make sure oil is good and hot.
Spoon batter in oil.
Keep turning until golden brown.
Serve with applesauce and sprinkle with sugar.

title: steamed broccoli
directions: Arrange broccoli in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cover and steam 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, Jiffy mix, eggs, butter, 1/2 sour cream and 1/2 grated cheese.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Spread top with remaining sour cream, then remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mary lou lange's spaghetti sauce for 100
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Combine all ingredients; simmer. Use with 15 pounds of spaghetti noodles, 10 loaves French bread, 3 bags salad and 2 quarts of salad dressing.

title: 15 minute pickles
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, salt and spice. Bring to a boil.
Put cucumbers, onions and peppers in alternate layers in 1-quart jars.
Pour boiling liquid over all.
Seal and refrigerate.

title: chocolate-banana meal-in-a-muffin(contains all 4 food groups)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, blending until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir just until mixed.
Put into 12 muffin tins sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: marinated pork roast
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pork loin, in a jar and shake well, making sure all is well blended.
Pour over pork loin and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Turn pork several times.
Place meat, fat side up, on rack in a greased shallow roasting pan; reserve marinade.
Roast in a 325° oven for about 3 hours.
Baste pork with marinade several times while roasting.
Marinade forms very dark crust on roast.
This is one of my family's favorites.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well with spoon.
Add coconut, then buttermilk. Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: raspberry poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and spoon over cake in pan.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Top with thawed Cool Whip.
Garnish with raspberries or colored sprinkles.
Serves 8.

title: beef and vegetable fried rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick coating.
Mix Ricotta cheese, cottage cheese, parsley and garlic. Pour 1 cup of sauce in bottom of pan.
Arrange 1/3 of the noodles in the pan so that they touch, but do not overlap.
Spread 1/2 of the cheese mixture over the noodles.
Top with 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese.
Top this with 1 cup of sauce, 1/3 of the noodles, then remainder of cheese mixture and the rest of the Mozzarella cheese.
Add another cup of sauce, another layer of noodles and the remainder of the sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered lightly with aluminum foil, for 1 hour. Yields 12 servings.

title: poppy seed torte
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crust).
Cook until thick.
Pour over crust.
Beat 4 egg whites, stiff.
Add 8 teaspoons sugar, two at a time.
Spread over filling.
Bake until egg whites are brown.

title: guacamole
directions: Cut stem ends off tomatoes and hollow out, leaving 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick shells.
Discard seeds.
Chop tomato pulp and tops. Set aside.

Halve, seed, peel and cut the avocado into chunks. Combine the chunks, cottage cheese, lemon juice, garlic, salt and pepper sauce in blender or food processor until mixture is smooth. Stir in chopped tomato.
Makes 16 (2 tablespoon) servings of dip.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Put a layer of graham crackers on bottom.
Blend pudding and milk, then blend Cool Whip in pudding.
Put a layer of pudding, then a layer of crackers, then last layer of pudding.
Melt chocolate frosting and pour over top.

title: crab and cheese spread
directions: Soften cheese and spread on a dinner plate.
Sprinkle crab meat over cheese.
Mix catsup and horseradish and spread over all. Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder. Beat eggs; add sugar, vanilla and oil. Then add zucchini. Add dry ingredients. Mix well. Pour into 2 ungreased loaf pans. Cook about 1 hour.

title: peanut bars
directions: Melt over hot water the milk, chocolate chips and oleo.
When melted, add marshmallows and peanuts.
Mix together.
Press in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies well and set aside.
Cream powdered sugar, cream cheese and oleo together and set aside.
Mix Cool Whip, milk and pudding mix together and set aside.
Layer in 8-inch diameter flower pot or plastic bowl.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello and let stand until it starts to thicken. Grind and dice rest of the ingredients.
Add sugar to ground cranberries, oranges, apples and celery (finely chopped).
Add all ingredients to jello and chill.

title: tater tot bake
directions: In skillet, brown the meat and onion; drain fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with potatoes.
Combine soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch round or square baking dish.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, stirring until blended.
Spoon over batter.
Do not stir.
Add fruit. Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: cajun crawfish etoufee
directions: Melt butter, then add onion and bell pepper. Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of mushroom soup. Bring to a boil. Lower fire to medium heat and let cook for 20 minutes. Add crawfish and cook for 15 minutes or until crawfish is tender. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the shortening, butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Add the flour, alternating with the 7-Up.
Add the flavorings and bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chili corn bread bake
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.

Drain. Add onion and green pepper. Cook for several minutes, stirring often. Stir in salt, seasoning mix and tomato sauce. Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine muffin mix and evaporated milk in a bowl.
Mix well.
Spread evenly over casserole. Top with cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Divide into 4 portions forming each into a patty.
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Heat oil over high heat, reduce heat to medium and add patties.
Cook, turning once, until browned, about 3 minutes on each side.
Serve on warmed platter with a seafood sauce.
Yield: 2 servings of 2 patties each.

title: easy pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except the pecans and cook at a low temperature until the sugar is dissolved.
Then boil until the soft ball stage is reached.
Add pecans.
Stir until it just begins to harden.
This candy hardens very quickly once it has started to thicken in the pan.
Quickly drop by spoonfuls into 2-inch patties on wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 4 minutes.
Drain.
Place in buttered casserole. Place grated cheese on broccoli.
Add milk and cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Place onion rings on top and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: "stuffed cabbage" casserole
directions: Brown the meat with onion in oil until meat is browned.
Drain well and add seasonings.
In greased casserole, alternate layers of cabbage and meat mixture. Pour tomato soup over all. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(If desired, add 2 cups cooked rice alternating with other ingredients.)

title: french dip sandwich
directions: Remove all visible fat.
Place roast in slow cooker.
Combine soy sauce, bouillon and spices.
Pour over roast, add water to almost cover roast.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 to 12 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat from broth, reserve broth, shred meat with fork and serve on hard rolls or French bread.
Dip into broth.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook beef, onion and garlic until beef is no longer pink, stirring occasionally to break up meat.
Drain.
Add beans, salsa, chili powder and oregano.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve topped with cheese.

title: wyoming whopper cookies
directions: *I use Jif brand peanut butter.
If unavailable, use another brand, but add several tablespoons water to mixture.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Peel orange.
Remove seed and skin.
Combine sugar, shortening, orange, orange juice, eggs, soda, salt and flour in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on and ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees until lightly brown. Remove from oven and cool slightly.
Transfer cookies to rack to cool completely.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pineapple in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place pie filling on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over; sprinkle nuts over the cake mix.
Cut up oleo over all.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute first three ingredients in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer one hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits; roll in cinnamon and sugar that have been mixed together.
Put in greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter, brown sugar and water; boil 2 minutes and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: frozen pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in pie crusts.
Freezer several hours until firm.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Color half of frosting red and half yellow.
Pile coconut and green food coloring in sandwich bag and work coloring in for lettuce.
Frost bottom half of 1/2 vanilla wafer with yellow and half red.
Sandwich wafers with grasshopper cookie in between and coconut for lettuce. Boil water (1/2 cup water and 1 tablespoon sugar).
Cool.
Brush on top of top wafer.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Adjust salt to taste.
Serve with chips.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 casserole dish with pam spray and line dish with crescent rolls.
Layer on top of rolls, sausage then cheese. Mix eggs and milk and pour over cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in preheated oven at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and garlic in large saucepan or Dutch oven until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Add tomatoes; break up with a fork.
Stir in tomato sauce, 2 tablespoons parsley flakes, the sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and the basil.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour, or until mixture is the consistency of spaghetti sauce.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Divide nuts and morsels in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Over this pour mixture of margarine, eggs, sugar, syrup and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; may take less time.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine 2 cups raisins, 3 cups boiling water and 2/3 cup sugar and boil 10 minutes.
Add cornstarch, mixed in a little water, 1 egg, nutmeg and butter.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Put into unbaked pie shell and add top crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 400° and continue baking until crust is brown.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, preserves and cinnamon. Combine soda and buttermilk; add to mixture, then add flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: yam and carrot tsimmes
directions: Cook carrots and yams until tender.
Drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Layer in a baking dish with brown sugar between layers.
Add water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Remove cover and continue baking until top is golden brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Stir together well cranberry sauce, pineapple and sugar.
Add chopped bananas and nuts.
Stir well.
Defrost Cool Whip and fold into mixture until all fruit is combined with the Cool Whip.
Pour into plastic container (or several smaller containers) and freeze. Allow to sit out at room temperature about 20 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend well. Add dry ingredients and mix only until mixture is smooth.
Spread into greased large baking dish.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 23 minutes.

title: munchos nachos
directions: On a large microwave-safe plate, arrange 8 to 10 tortilla chips or as many as will fit in one layer.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon salsa in center of each chip.
Top with a few pieces of tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat until all tortilla chips are topped, making 4 plates in all.
Microwave each plate on High for 1 minute or until cheese is melted.
Remove plate carefully as it may be hot.
Top each nacho with about 1 tablespoon sour cream.
Serve immediately.

title: crock-pot meal to serve over noodles
directions: Cut meat in pieces.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over meat. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve over noodles.
Can cook in crock-pot on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: creamy chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Spread rice in a buttered, shallow 1- 1/2 quart baking dish.
Arrange asparagus over rice.
Top with chicken.
Blend soup, sour cream, milk, lemon juice and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: sweet 'n hot mustard
directions: Combine dry mustard with vinegar in glass bowl (do not use aluminum).
Mix well and let stand for about 1 hour.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Combine all ingredients in double boiler or nonstick pan and cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes or desired thickness.
Makes about 2 cups.
Keeps in refrigerator for months.

title: egg casserole
directions: Great to make the night before.

title: kahlua cheesecake
directions: Blend cream cheese on low of electric mixer.
When well blended add flour, salt, cocoa and half of sugar.
Separate egg whites and yolks.
On low speed, blend whipping cream, egg yolks and kahlua. Blend well; mix cream cheese mixture.
On high speed in another bowl beat egg whites with remaining sugar until stiff.
Fold in cheese mixture.
Cover bottom of pan with aluminum foil.
Grease sides of pan.
Make crust of graham cracker and margarine.
Pat 1/2-inch thick into bottom of pan.
Spoon in cheese mixture into crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: chocolate chess pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pie shells until sugar dissolves.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Center will be soft and set up as cools.
Makes 2.

title: buttered breadsticks
directions: In a medium bowl, combine 1 1/3 cups flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Gradually add milk. Stir in the remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a lightly floured board. Knead gently for 1/2 minute. Roll into a 1/4-inch thick rectangle. Cut in half widthwise, then cut each lengthwise into 6 strips. Brush one side with butter. Place, butter side down, on a greased baking sheet. Butter other side and fold each strip nearly in half. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 1 dozen.

title: sesame potato spears
directions: Pare and cut potatoes in strips.
Grease a cookie sheet and place potatoes on the sheet, arranging them so they do not touch. Brush with melted butter. Sprinkle salt, paprika and sesame seed over the top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Turn, if you wish. Serves 6.

title: guacamole dip
directions: In small bowl, combine refried beans and chilies; spread on serving plate.
Combine sour cream and taco seasoning; spoon bean mixture, spreading evenly.
In another bowl, mash avocados; stir in lime juice and salt.
Spoon evenly over sour cream mixture. Cover; chill 3 hours.

title: mama's jam cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, Crisco, jam and eggs; mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or in 2 (9-inch) pans for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend wet ingredients.
Fold in dry ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: grandma bonnie's favorite cake
directions: Beat all ingredients except for 1/2 cup milk on low speed for 1 minute.
Add 1/2 cup milk and beat 1 more minute.
Pour into pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hummingbird cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine sugar with all other dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until moist; do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts, bananas and cherries. Spoon into three 9-inch cake pans (or tube pan) which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes for 3 layers or 1 hour for tube pan.
Use Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: beans and more
directions: Brown ground meat and drain off excess grease.
Brown bacon and onions.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook slowly 3 to 4 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: *Important to use escarole as it will not wilt.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine, stirring well. Spoon sauce evenly over chicken and sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: white jello
directions: Cream sugar and cheese together; add vanilla and milk. Dissolve gelatine in boiling water; add cold water.
Set aside. Let cool but not set.
To the cream cheese mixture add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
When gelatine is cool, add to mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate.

title: seedless grapes in sour cream
directions: Wash and stem grapes.
