Put in glass bowl.
Top with sour cream and sprinkle with sugar.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: quick chili relleno
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1-quart baking dish.
Place 1/2 of cheese in baking dish and cover with chilies. Pour eggs over cheese and chilies. Add the stewed tomatoes.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and slightly brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients with milk until stiff enough to drop into hot oil or grease. Fry until golden brown.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix, dry jello and boiling water.
Bring to a boil.
Let boil for one minute.
Cool.
Blend in Cool Whip and oranges.
Pour into dish or mold.
Can be made ahead and holds up well.

title: chinese barbecue sauce for fish
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Let fish marinate in sauce 30 minutes to 2 hours or longer.
Broil fish, basting with marinade.
Makes 2 1/2 cups sauce.

title: grandma's chops
directions: Brown pork chops on stove top.
Place a layer in deep baking dish, top with sliced onion rings and top that with tomato soup. Repeat until dish is full, usually 4 to 5 layers.
Bake uncovered at 475° until mixture bubbles, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 1 hour, covered.
Serve with baked potatoes; use juices for topping.

title: yummy peanut butter cookies(diabetic cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet lightly.
Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Work margarine and peanut butter with spoon until creamy; gradually add brown sugar substitute, continue working until light.
Add regular sugar substitute and egg; beat well.
Mix in dry ingredients thoroughly. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased heavy-duty aluminum foil; flatten with tines of fork.
Bake about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: kraut slaw
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar until completely dissolved.
Allow to cool.
Pour over first 5 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and chill well.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown and drain fat from ground beef. Add onion and garlic powder. Add to preceeding ingredients the taco seasoning mix, tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste, green chilies and tomato sauce. Simmer 5 minutes. Spoon in flour tortillas and roll up. Place in oblong pan. If you have meat mixture left over, spoon over tortillas.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard and pepper.
Pour over hot carrots.
Add chopped celery, onion and green pepper. Keeps up to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: tuna broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in casserole.
Spread tuna over the top.
Add one-half can of the mushroom soup, the stuffing mix and then the rest of the soup.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake in a 350° oven for one hour.
Serves four.

title: old fashion devil's food cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 round pans or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan with Pam.
In a large mixing bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove beater.
Stir in boiling water. Batter will be thin.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in round pans 30 to 35 minutes or 35 to 40 minutes in an oblong pan, or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan to a wire rack.
Cool completely.
Frost with frosting of your choice.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
(This is easy to double).

title: jam sandwich
directions: Place bologna on top of one slice of bread.
Carefully center the second slice of bread over the bologna and then jam it together.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken; let cool. Take off the bone. Cook noodles in broth of chicken. Saut bell pepper in butter. Add enough flour and milk to make a white sauce. It should be thick but not lumpy. Melt cheese in this mixture while it is hot. Then add cream of mushroom soup. Combine all ingredients and place in a large casserole dish. Top with corn flake crumbs. Bake at 350° until bubbly hot.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set for at least eight hours.

title: cafe-rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, coffee and butter in a double boiler for about 25 minutes.
Combine all ingredients, except cinnamon; pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Set casserole in pan of warm water.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Turn off heat; let stand in oven for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water for 45 minutes or until tender.
Let cool to touch; peel and mash.
Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Spoon into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, then combine brown sugar, pecan, flour and 2 tablespoons of butter; sprinkle mixture over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon ice
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Add remaining sugar and lemon juice.
Mix well.
In blender, puree ice.
Add enough lemonade mixture to satisfy your taste.
Makes 4 drinks.

title: sunny fruit fiesta
directions: Use melon baller. Scoop flesh from cantaloupe and honeydew into balls and set aside.
In a large glass bowl, combine sugar, lime juice, lemon juice, orange liqueur and lime zest.

Stir well to dissolve sugar. Add cantaloupe balls, honeydew balls, strawberries and grapes. Toss gently. Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavors, stirring once or twice.
Spoon fruit mixture into serving bowls or hollowed out melon halves. Serve immediately.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted margarine. Press into
x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 stick softened margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Beat with mixer for 15 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Slice
bananas lengthwise and lay side by side on previous layer.
Drain pineapple, lay over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts.
Top with cherries.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and carrots.
Sift cake mix, pudding and cinnamon.
Mix all together.
Bake in 3 round cake layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease round layer pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch or square pan, 8 x 8 x 2 or 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Blend all ingredients; beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Add blueberries (roll lightly in flour so they will not sink).

title: texas pete hot wingers
directions: Cut wings at all joints. Throw away wing tips. Place wings on paper towels to absorb all water.

title: spanish fried rice
directions: Soak rice in hot water for 1/2 hour; drain well.
Spread in big shallow pan to dry a little, about 1 hour.
Cook bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
Add rice to drippings and cook until rice is lightly browned.
Add crumbled bacon, beef broth, tomato sauce, green pepper, onion, garlic and cumin seed.
Cover; cook over low heat, stirring now and then, until rice is done and liquid absorbed, about 30 minutes (add extra water if needed).

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground meat in large frying pan, breaking it up as it cooks.
Drain fat.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Saute with meat until tender.
Add tomato juice, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Add salsa in amount necessary to make spicy for your taste.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Add rice and olives.
Stir, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, at least five minutes before serving.

title: danish sweet rolls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients like pie crust. Add the eggs, milk and yeast mixture.
Beat.
Add 1 cup flour. Dough will be soft. Let set in refrigerator for several hours. Take out. Cut into 4 parts and roll out each part (like pie crust).
Spread with butter.
Cut into triangular wedges.
Roll each wedge from wide side to point. Let rise and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost and sprinkle with nuts.

title: baked pizza no. 2
directions: Make dough.
Spread on pizza pan.

Cover with onions, which have been sliced and fried in oil, and garlic, pepper and salt. Lay on top of dough slices of fresh tomatoes with a few pitted ripe olives and a few filleted anchovies (washed of salt).
Add several strips of pimentos.
Bake in hot (400°) oven for 1/2 hour.

title: jalapeno hominy
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan and bring to a boil. Stir often to mix cheese.
Serve immediately.
Delicious!

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into small bite-size pieces.
Add and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake about 30 minutes or until done at 350°.
Can be served hot or cold. Fresh fruit garnish makes it more tempting.

title: best-ever cake layer
directions: In a large mixing bowl, with an electric mixer, blend ingredients at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Caramel or 7 Minute Icing.

title: everything cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add chicken or turkey, celery, peas, onions and green peppers.
Pile lightly in a casserole dish. Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Heat 5 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: dump cake
directions: You will need 1 pan, size 12 3/4 x 9 x 2-inches (or approximately).

title: shrimp mold
directions: Grease mold with mayonnaise.
Heat tomato soup and cream cheese until softened.
Add mayonnaise while still warm, then add rest of ingredients.
Gelatine is last to be added.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from mold when ready to use.
Serve with crackers.

title: french strawberry pie(no sugar)
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Wash and cap strawberries.
Add sweetener.
Press 1 1/2 cups strawberries through strainer.
Add food coloring.
If desired, add lemon juice and bring to boil. Remove from heat and soften gelatin, stirring to dissolve. Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in remaining whole strawberries.
Spoon in cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate until set. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: grandma merritt's famous lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add milk.
Slowly add flour*.
When mixed well, add flavorings.
(*With salt and baking powder.)

title: lentil-spinach stew
directions: Rinse lentils; set aside.
In a large saucepan or Dutch oven cook onion and garlic until tender, not brown.
Stir in lentils, water, tomatoes, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce, salt, thyme, fennel seed, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add carrots and frozen spinach. Bring to a boil, breaking up spinach with a fork; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for about 10 minutes or until lentils are tender. Add vinegar; discard bay leaf.
Makes 4 servings.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well with pastry blender, fork or mixer.
Mix until mixture is like small peas.
In small bowl, beat together vinegar, egg & water.
Combine with the flour mixture until it is blended well.
Divide into 5 portions and shape into flat patties.
Wrap well in plastic or foil. Refrigerate or freeze.
Will keep in refrigerator a week or months in freezer.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, milk, seasoned salt and pepper.
Mix well; set aside.
Mix cauliflower, broken up in small pieces, onion, peas and celery in a bowl.
Add mayonnaise mixture and mix well.
Set in refrigerator and chill.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Pour butter over topping ingredients and crumble over potato mixture.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: neighborhood casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hot chinese chicken salad
directions: Roll pieces of chicken in cornstarch.
Heat corn oil in frying pan or wok over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; quickly brown. Sprinkle with garlic.
Add tomato, water chestnuts, mushrooms, onions and celery; stir.
Sprinkle with Accent.
Stir in soy sauce. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add lettuce; toss.
Serve with rice.

title: animal cracker necklaces
directions: Melt candy coating.
Spread candy coating generously on flat side of 4 animal crackers.
Place one pretzel in the coating on each cracker, leaving top 2 holes of pretzel open to allow for threading ribbon of necklace.
Allow to set.
Repeat with remaining candy, animal crackers and pretzels.
Great for rainy days!

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serve with goldfish crackers.

title: low-fat macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine rest of ingredients and fold in macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all of the dry ingredients in a bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir well until moistened.
Stir in strawberries and pecans.
Pour batter into 2 lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Bring egg whites to room temperature.
Beat together; add sugar slowly.
Add salt.
Beat 7 minutes in a double boiler; then add vanilla and nut meats.
Place by tablespoonful on oleo-greased cookie sheet, 1 inch apart.
Bake in a slow 275° oven for 1 hour or until dry.
If not dry, allow 10 minutes more.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook green bell pepper slices, onion and garlic in shortening in covered skillet over low heat until tender.
Stir in soup, water, lemon juice, seasoning and shrimp.
Cook about 10 minutes. Stir often.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: rosenberry steak marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour over steak.
Marinate overnight or as long as you wish.
We marinate it for up to 2 days.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Stir in Stove Top cornbread stuffing.
Set aside 1 cup of stuffing and oleo.

title: gooey chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
This is a double batch.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs, soda and pineapple (and juice) with mixer on low speed.
Then add nuts. Pour into a 9 x 12 inch greased pan and bake for 40 minutes.
Stir together brown sugar, cream cheese and margarine with spoon.
Put frosting on cake while cake is still hot.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Put the ingredients in the order shown in crock-pot.
Turn on high until it starts to boil, then turn to low for 4 or 5 hours. Or, leave on low all day.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper in skillet.
Drain off grease and put in a slow cooker.
Then add cheese, tomato sauce and chiles.
Mix until cheese is melted.
Serve warm.
Dip in your favorite chips.

title: diet cream cheese ball
directions: Chop onion and beef.
Mix with cream cheese.
Form in ball.

title: noodles
directions: Roll very thin on a floured board.
Sprinkle a little flour on dough and let dry for 30 minutes.
Cut and drop into broth.
Let boil over slow fire for 30 minutes without raising lid.

title: applesauce-pecan bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Mix 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and next 4 ingredients.
Gradually add to first mixture, beat with spoon until well mixed.
Stir in 1 cup nuts and the fruit.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix remaining nuts, cinnamon and the brown sugar.
Sprinkle evenly on top of batter and press lightly with hand.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
To keep top from getting too brown, spread piece of foil over top during last 1/2 hour of baking.
Wrap in foil and store in refrigerator, will keep about one week.

title: chicken breasts in champagne
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with palm of hand.
Combine flour, salt and pepper and dust breasts on both sides.
Saute full side down in butter and oil for 5 minutes, shaking the pan to prevent sticking.
Turn the chicken and add champagne.
Cook for about 15 minutes until chicken is done and champagne is reduced by half. Remove to heated platter and keep warm.
Add the cream to the pan juices and cook until thickened.
Add sauteed mushrooms and pour sauce over the chicken.
Serves 6.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: In a blender, mix all ingredients, except coconut.
Pour into greased fluted pie plate. Sprinkle with 2 to 3 cups flaked coconut.
Bake in a 350° oven covered with aluminum foil for 20 minutes.
Continue baking uncovered for additional 15 to 20 minutes until cake test comes out clean.
Refrigerate overnight. Enjoy!

title: easy-make cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and use to dust a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Mix butter and other flavoring with milk in a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat for 20 minutes.
Pour batter into pan and place in a cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken vegetables stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok or skillet over high heat.
Add garlic and cook a few seconds, then add frozen vegetables and stir frequently until warmed through.
Cut chicken into 1/2 x 2-inch strips.
When vegetables are barely cooked, add chicken and stir until it becomes opaque.
Stir in teriyaki sauce and serve over hot rice.

title: apricot bonbons
directions: Combine
coconut,
apricots
and
milk	in
large bowl. Cover. Refrigerate
at least 4 hours or overnight.
Roll into balls using
scant tablespoon.
Place on wax paper and refrigerate. Melt almond
bark and dip balls using a fork and swirl the top with a toothpick.

title: mother's garden goulash
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large iron skillet; cover and cook on medium heat until vegetables are almost done.
Remove lid; reduce heat and cook until thick.

title: coconut cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix.	Add 1 package frozen coconut to batter.
Bake as directed on cake mix.
Punch holes in cake.
Pour can of cream of coconut over hot cake.
Let cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.	Top with package of frozen coconut.

title: "nanie's" hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs and blend in sugar, 1 cup at a time; mix well.
Melt butter in 1 cup of hot milk.
Cool a bit, then add to egg-sugar mixture.
Mix flour and baking powder together.
Add to egg, sugar and butter mixture slowly.

title: veal chops with mushrooms(makes 4 servings)
directions: *Try shoulder and rib chops, approximately 2 1/2 pounds.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate in refrigerator for 2 days.

title: spanish potatoes
directions: Fry in butter or margarine the green pepper, pimentos and onion.
Add potatoes, ham, salt and paprika.
Continue frying until browned.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Drain bacon and crumble; set aside.
Cook onion in bacon fat until tender; drain.
Mix beans, brown sugar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion together in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours. Stir.
Top with bacon.
Let stand before serving.

title: artichoke quiche
directions: Cut artichoke hearts in half.
Blend artichokes with eggs, crab meat or pepperoni, salt, pepper and cheeses. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set. Serve warm or cold.

title: sweet potatoes(caramel glazed)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange sweet potatoes in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Season with salt. Spoon caramel topping on potatoes. Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes, basting occasionally with caramel topping in pan.
Makes 4 servings.

title: savory roast potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch baking pan.
Pare potatoes; roll in butter to coat well.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Remove pan from oven; turn potatoes.
Add chicken broth.
Bake 1 hour longer, turning several times.
Makes 8 servings.

title: east arkansas cheese straws
directions: Place butter in mixing bowl and sift flour over butter.
Work flour and butter with fingers until it reaches the consistency of cornmeal.
Add grated cheese, work until a smooth consistency is reached.
Put in spritz gun cookie press with star shaped template. Extrude onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven, about 250° to 275° until dry throughout.
Do not let cheese straws brown.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Beat together margarine, sugar and eggs. Add pineapple and coconut. Mix and pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add melted butter and blend well.
Stir in eggs, chips, nuts and vanilla.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serve with a dab of whipped topping.
Best served warm.
Very rich!

title: apple impromtuv
directions: Put apple pie filling on bottom of 8-inch square cake pan. Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture over top of pie filling. Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry conserve
directions: In a large skillet cook and stir brown sugar, margarine or butter and vinegar over medium heat for 1 or 2 minutes.
Add onions.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat for 10 to 12 minutes or until onions are glazed and tender, stirring often.
Set aside.

title: yellow cake(nice and fluffy)
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt and set aside. Cream together the margarine, Crisco, 2/3 cup milk and vanilla extract.
Mix creamed mixture and flour mixture together until creamy. Add eggs and 1/4 cup milk and mix well. Bake 20 to 25 minutes for layers (9-inch pans) or 35 to 40 minutes for loaf pans in a 350° oven.

title: pizza sandwiches
directions: Cook sausage until pink is gone.
Add seasonings.
Spread on rye bread and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: no bake instant pumpkin pie
directions: Add vanilla pudding to milk in bowl. Beat at lowest speed just until blended, about 30 seconds. Blend in pumpkin, spice and 2 cups Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell. Chill until set, at least 4 hours. Garnish with remaining Cool Whip and pecan halves. Enjoy.

title: diabetic apple crisp
directions: Arrange apple slices in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix together the Equal, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until well blended.
Sprinkle flour mixture over apples.
Sprinkle lemon juice over all, then pat until firm on top.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Turn dish every 5 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serves 16.
Contains 123 calories per serving.

title: fresh kielbasa and sauerkraut
directions: In a large kettle, place kielbasa and cover with water.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer for about 2 1/2 hours.
While kielbasa is cooking, in a large skillet, saute onions until clear; add sauerkraut, applesauce*, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
When kielbasa is done, cut into 2-inch pieces and add to sauerkraut.
Also, add about 1 cup of water that kielbasa was cooked in.
Continue for another 15 minutes.
Serve with boiled potatoes (quartered) and bakery fresh pumpernickel bread.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Fold sour cream, soup mix, water chestnuts and spices into spinach.
Bake for 30 minutes, uncovered, at 325°.
Top with grated cheese for the last 10 minutes of baking.
Serves 6.

title: jiffy apple crisp
directions: Cut margarine into mix making sure its mixed thoroughly. Place pie filling in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: caramel glazed pear cake
directions: Toss together diced pears and one tablespoon sugar, let stand 5 minutes. Beat eggs, 2 cups sugar, cinnamon and oil at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended. Combine flour, salt, baking soda and add to egg mixture. Beat until blended. Fold pecans, pears and vanilla extract. Pour batter into greased and floured 10 inch Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Remove from pan and drizzle caramel glaze over warm cake.

title: apricot sauce
directions: Wash and cook apricots in water as directed on package.
Put the cooked apricots through a food mill, or puree them, about 3/4 cup at a time in a blender (or use a food processor).
Add sugar and salt.
Stir and cook 4 to 5 minutes over moderate heat.
Add Cognac or apricot brandy to taste.
Serve over puddings, or plain cake.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: frozen cucumber slices
directions: Mix together sliced cucumbers, onion and salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Rinse and mix well. Mix sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over cucumbers and freeze in small individual containers.

title: delicious candy
directions: Boil cream until it is reduced to 2 tablespoons.
Remove from heat; stir in Grand Marnier and chocolate.
Return to low heat to melt chocolate.
Whisk in butter.
When mixture is smooth, pour into bowl; refrigerate 1 hour.
When mixture is firm, shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in cocoa.
Store truffles, covered, in refrigerator.
Let truffles stand at room temperature 1 hour before serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in 9-inch unbaked pie shell at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chinese spareribs
directions: Have ribs sliced at joints.
Rub split garlic cloves into meat.
Baste with sauce and broil until done.

title: grandma wade's oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the margarine, sugars, peanut butter, eggs and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. When well mixed, fold in the chocolate chips, raisins and nuts, if desired. Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool on pan for 1 minute, then remove to rack.
Freeze in covered container.

title: medallions of pork with riesling sauce
directions: Season pork with salt and pepper.
Coat in the flour; shake off excess.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic and saute until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to bowl.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in same skillet over medium-high heat.
Add pork and saute about 4 minutes per side.
Transfer pork to plate. Add onion mixture, Riesling, raisins, vinegar, green peppercorns and herbs to same skillet and boil until sauce thickens, about 4 minutes.
Add pork to skillet to heat through.
Divide pork among plates.
Add 1/4 cup butter to sauce in skillet and whisk just until melted.
Mix in pine nuts.
Spoon sauce over pork.

title: doughnuts
directions: To the sour cream, add the soda, then add sugar and eggs. Beat well.
Sift 1 cup flour, salt and baking powder.
Add sweet milk and extract.
Beat well and then add enough flour to make a soft dough that can be handled.
Roll and cut, fry in deep fat and roll in powdered sugar to which a little cinnamon has been added.

title: sweet 'n sour pork
directions: Brown pork.
Add water.
Cover, simmer until tender.
Drain pineapple.
Reserve liquid.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Add to pork.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add pineapple, green pepper and onion. Cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: aplets
directions: Combine grated apples with sugar in heavy pan.
Slowly bring to boil.
Soften gelatin in applesauce.
Add to cooked apple mix. Bring to full boil for 15 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until fluffy.
Then add the remainder of the ingredients, lastly the pecans.
Pour in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°; 35 minutes at 350°.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Grease large casserole dish.
Slice eggplant thin.
Do same to onion.
Alternate eggplant, tomato sauce and cheese in layers until all ingredients are gone.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Recipe will make a large casserole.
May be cut in half.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Use 1 can soup and 16 oz. sour cream or 2 cans soup and 8 oz. sour cream or 2 cans soup and 16 oz. sour cream, depending on how much you want to make.

title: cocktail franks in whiskey sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve (use cocktail picks).

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix and store in a jar.
Add 2 teaspoons to one cup of hot water.

title: filled hungarian cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients oleo, cheese and flour together until mixed thoroughly.
Roll on floured board of mixed flour and powdered sugar.
Cut into 2-inch squares or 2-inch circles with cookie cutter.
Place 1/2 teaspoon filling on each and fold 2 sides towards center.
Press hard enough to hold.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Add beaten egg to milk.
Mix dry ingredients; sift.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix slightly.
Add blueberries.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with mixture of paprika, salt, pepper, ginger and flour.
Brown in lard in skillet.
Add pineapple juice and vinegar.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Simmer for 40 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Place sugars, water and butter in a pan over high heat.
Boil for 2 minutes or to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add pecans and vanilla.
Beat until mixture becomes creamy and begins to sugar on sides of pan, then drop by spoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: fried beaver tail
directions: Heat the tail in a moderately warm oven (about 300°), until the skin puffs and peels off.
Boil until the meat is easily removed from the bone.
Cut meat into cubes, salt and pepper.
Dip into egg and then flour.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve the Knox gelatine in the cold water.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add gelatine; stir well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch
dish.
Chill until set.
Cut with knife or cookie cutters.

title: friendship salad
directions: Pour liquid over vegetables and refrigerate for several hours.

title: christmas day sausage ring
directions: Lightly grease a 7 inch ring mold.
Sprinkle cornflakes in bottom of mold.
Mix sausage, onion, bread crumbs, parsley and egg.
Pat meat mixture into mold.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Drain and bake another 15 minutes or until done. Invert mold onto heated platter, garnish with fresh parsley.
Fill center with scrambled eggs if desired.
Sausage ring may be refrigerated or frozen before baking.
Thaw and heat as directed.

title: "tsourekia" - easter bread
directions: In large saucepan, warm milk.
When milk is warm, add salt, yeast and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Stir until yeast is melted.
Put aside and let rise for 1 hour.
When 1 hour is up, add the eggs, sugar, melted butter, lemon and orange peels.
Stir in well with hand, not mixer.
When everything is mixed in, begin adding flour slowly until it makes a soft nonsticky dough.
Knead well.
Put aside to rise 3 to 4 hours.
When well risen, knead again.
Shape into braids or loaves.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar.
Put butter in casserole dish and put in oven to melt.

title: roast chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken; crush garlic, ginger, pepper and salt. Combine with cinnamon, turmeric, cloves, vinegar and butter.
Rub this mixture all over chicken and allow to stand for 30 minutes. Place chicken in roasting tray together with margarine and cook in moderately hot oven for 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally.

title: cheesy hashburgers
directions: About 20 minutes before serving, preheat broiler.
Blend hash, sour cream or yogurt, relish and horseradish. Set aside.
Place halved buns, cut side up, on cookie sheet.
Spread each half with some mustard.
Spread one side of each bun with hash mixture.
On the other side, lay a tomato slice, topped with a slice of cheese. Broil until cheese is bubbly, then serve at once.
Serve with French green beans, salad, pears and cookies.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and berries and let stand.
Drain juice off berries and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Cook a little, then add Junket mix.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add berries and put in baked pie shell.
Add whipped cream for topping.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches and butter in 2-quart baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients in blender on high for 15 to 20 seconds. Pour over peaches and butter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: ham salad
directions: Using a meat grinder, grind up eggs, pickles and bologna.
Add sugar and Miracle Whip; mix well.
Store in refrigerator until well chilled.
Spread on bread and enjoy!

title: winter soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pasta.
Simmer for 2 hours. Add pasta until heated through.
Serve hot with cornbread and salad.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Can add any vegetables that you like.

title: avocado dressing
directions: Peel and pit avocado.
Mash thoroughly.
Stir in lime juice, green chiles, cumin, garlic salt and Italian dressing.
Mix with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in additional Italian dressing as needed to make the right consistency.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups dressing.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add syrup and salt; beat well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: greta's pasta with vegetables
directions: Saute quickly in a pan (preferably on gas, high heat), stirring often.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in baking dish.
Top with chili and then cheese.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add condensed milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with chilled cherry pie filling before serving.

title: pennsylvania chili (sweet)
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in large pot and bring to boil. Simmer until vegetables are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, brown hamburger and drain fat.
When vegetables are tender, add cooked hamburger and undrained kidney beans.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes and add chili powder to taste (depends on how hot you like it).

title: apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix in order given, adding flour mixture last.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add other ingredients in large bowl and stir thoroughly.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured (or Pam sprayed) glass Pyrex.
Can also put into Bundt pan that has been Pam sprayed.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Test by toothpick. Allow cake to cool before icing.

title: belgium vegetables
directions: Heat until sugar dissolves, then let cool and pour over vegetable mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator for 8 hours and serve.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: rock candy
directions: You will need an 11 x 13-inch baking sheet.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Stir soup and milk until smooth.
Mix in 1/2 can French fried onions, beans and pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes. Sprinkle remaining onion on top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: aunt sally's red devil's food
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar; cream thoroughly.
Add eggs and cocoa, alternately.
Add flour, sour milk and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: soup bean salad
directions: In a large pan, crumble corn bread and top with beans, then tomatoes, peppers, onions and bacon.
Set aside.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and green pepper in butter until tender, stir in tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add shrimp.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice. Yields 6 servings.

title: carrots with orange sauce
directions: Clean carrots well.
Slice and cook.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour over cooked carrots. Cover and let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: maple glazed chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings into 3 sections; discard wing tip section. In a large, resealable plastic bag or shallow glass container, combine remaining ingredients. Reserve 1 cup for basting and refrigerate. Add chicken to the remaining marinade and turn to coat. Seal bag or cover container; refrigerate for 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain and discard marinade.

title: almond tea punch
directions: Boil water and steep tea 5 minutes. Add sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and almond extract to tea. Add the water and stir well. Freeze. Remove from freezer in time to allow it to become slushy at serving time.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook or steam zucchini in boiling salted water, until just tender.
Drain.
In microwave casserole dish (1-quart size), melt 4 tablespoons of butter or margarine.
Add carrot and onion and cook until tender.
Stir in 2 1/4 cups stuffing cubes, soup and carrot/onion.
Mix into zucchini dish, stirring gently.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Add remaining 1 1/4 cups stuffing cubes to butter and toss gently.
Sprinkle cubes on casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered. Makes 6 to 10 servings.

title: turkey breast tenderloins
directions: In a bowl, mix cracker crumbs, garlic powder and Season-All. In separate bowl, beat egg and water with a fork.

title: rice mushroom sausage skillet dinner
directions: Cook
onion and sausage balls in skillet until onion is tender and sausage is lightly browned.
Drain off excess fat. Add
next 4 ingredients.
Heat to boiling, cover, reduce heat and
simmer 20
minutes.
Add
peas
and pimientos, cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chantilly mayonnaise
directions: Put mayonnaise in bowl.
Whip cream shortly before serving and add to mayonnaise.

title: lime salad(excellent)
directions: Mix Jell-O and cream cheese with boiling water until dissolved.
Smooth with an electric mixer.
Add in remaining ingredients and stir with a spoon.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Add Ragu sauce to cooked beef.
In greased 13 x 9-inch pan, layer 3 noodles, beef sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Make 4 layers.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spaghetti with tomatoes and goat cheese
directions: Cut tomatoes into chunks; add olive oil, garlic, hot pepper flakes, capers and salt to taste. Stir to blend. Cook pasta in salted water until al dente. Tear basil leaves into small pieces. Drain pasta and toss with goat cheese in a large bowl. Transfer into saucepan and saute 2 minutes on medium-high until garlic is released. Add basil and tomatoes. Toss and serve.

title: meat pies
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Mix all other ingredients; pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can use ham, shrimp or bacon in place of hamburger meat.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Stir in cranberry sauce, drained pineapple, celery and nuts.
Pour into mold or bowl, which has been rinsed out with cold water first. Chill in refrigerator until firm, overnight.
Remove from mold or brown and put on a chilled plate.
Put a dab of mayonnaise on top.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Tear cakes into pieces and place in oblong dish.
Mix cream cheese and condensed milk together until smooth.
Dribble almost all of this over cake.
Mix strawberries with remaining mixture and dribble over cake.
If wanted, sprinkle pecans over this. Refrigerate for about 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip and pecans. Refrigerate until serving.

title: ina's fish salad
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients for vinaigrette.
Set aside.

title: cheese straws
directions: Have cheese and butter at room temperature.
Mix together and blend well.
Add other ingredients and blend well.
Run through cookie press.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375°
for about 12 minutes.

title: no name casserole
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients together in skillet; drain.
Add next 6 ingredients to beef mixture.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: irene's fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow.
Mix thoroughly.
Put into 8 x 8-inch pan until set.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shell.* Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: chicken-zucchini stir-fry
directions: Put the oil in a large skillet.
Turn the heat to medium.
Add chicken.
Stir.
Cover the skillet.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add the zucchini, green peppers, onion and celery to the skillet.
Stir gently until the vegetables are coated with oil.
Cook until the chicken and vegetables are hot.
Put the lid on the skillet.
Turn the heat to low.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Cook until the zucchini is tender and firm.
If the mixture gets dry, add a little water.
If there is liquid in the skillet, cook with the lid off.
Add black and red pepper.
Stir gently.
Cut cheese and place on top, if desired.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter or oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let set 5 minutes, then dust with powdered sugar, about 2/3 cup.

title: janet's fruit cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, salt, orange extract and applesauce. Next, mix fruit with flour. Add dry ingredients with batter.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours and 45 minutes or until done.
Cover and store 1 month before eating.

title: ham and corn chowder
directions: Mix ham, milk, corn and soup in 3 qt. saucepan. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally; reduce heat to low. Simmer uncovered 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with onions.

title: big orange fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and margarine to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add white chocolate morsels and marshmallow cream.
Mix well.
Remove 1 to 1 1/2 cups of
mixture and set aside.
To remainder of mix, add flavorings and food coloring. Mix well and pour into 9 x 13 buttered pan.
Drop white chocolate by spoonfuls on top of the orange.
Swirl through with a knife. Chill and cut with knife.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Add water until desired consistency.
Season with garlic and black pepper to taste. Simmer until heated through and well blended.
Doubles well.

title: apple sauce cake
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Bake in small tube pan for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: chicken huntington
directions: Stew chicken; bone and cut into small pieces.
Cook macaroni, cheese, pimentos, peas and mushrooms.
Melt butter in saucepan and add flour and 2 cups of chicken broth.
Cook until thick and add to chicken mixture.
Mix thoroughly and place in buttered baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
The last 10 minutes, add grated cheese and cook until melted and bubbly.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender; drain.
Cook chicken breasts and cut into bite sizes.
Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish, 9 x 11-inch.
Place cooked chicken on top. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: angie's brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla in a large mixing bowl on high speed for 10 minutes.
Add flour, beating just to blend.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
(Do not overbake.) Cool in pan; then cut into squares.

title: fluffy rice and chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix mushroom soup and milk; reserve 1/2 cup of mixture.
Mix remaining soup mixture, the rice, mushrooms (with liquid) and half the onion soup mix.
Pour into an ungreased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken breasts; sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover with foil; bake 1 hour. Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer.
(Can use whole chicken, cut up.)

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Chill.

title: venison stew
directions: Place cubed venison in a large pot with plenty of water and let it boil while preparing vegetables.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper.
Cook until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add 2 tablespoons of browned flour and 1/2 cup of water; stir until thickened.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice up the potatoes and the onions.
Cook in a quart of water until done.
Then add 1/2 gallon of milk, then the parsley flakes and Cheez Whiz.
Salt and pepper to taste.
You may add leftover mashed potatoes if you have them.
Stir well for about 15 minutes.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter; saute garlic and green peppers.
Slowly add flour.
Add milk, one cup at a time.
Slice Velveeta and add, stirring until it melts.
Add chicken broth, broccoli and carrots. Simmer.
Do not boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Mix together margarine, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, onions and poppy seed.
Put ham and cheese in rolls as desired.
Pour mixture over rolls.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Heat for 20 minutes at 350°.
Best served warm.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix all together. Make into small biscuits and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon and egg casserole(microwave)
directions: Place bacon
in
9-inch
pie plate.
Cover loosely with microwavesafe paper towel.	Cook on High 3 minutes.
Drain off fat, reserving
tablespoon in small custard cup; set aside. Stir pepper and mushrooms into bacon; cover and cook on High 2 minutes.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chocolate chips, margarine or butter and corn syrup in medium size saucepan (stir over low heat until melted and smooth). Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies, mixing lightly until well coated.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Line bottom of dish with crumbled crackers.
Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Pour over crackers.
Mix egg, milk and cheese; pour over onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon curd
directions: Put sugar, eggs, lemon juice, butter or oleo and lemon rind in a heavy pan and stir together.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat. Slowly boil for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into jars and store in refrigerator.
Use on toast, etc.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Cook onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Add all of the other ingredients; put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: la creme whipped topping
directions: Pour evaporated milk into large metal bowl and place in freezer until ice crystals form along edge of bowl, minimum of 30 minutes.
Chill electric mixer beaters at the same time.
Remove bowl and beaters from freezer.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, over medium-high heat, cook and stir steak, mushrooms and onion in margarine until steak is browned and vegetables are tender.
Reduce heat to medium. Add flour; cook and stir 1 minute. Add water and bouillon; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in sour cream; heat through (do not boil). Serve over noodles.

title: ranch cracker snacks
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers and mix well.
Pour over crackers and make sure all are coated.
Place in sheet pan and cook in warm oven 20 to 30 minutes.
Store in airtight container and enjoy.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and then press firmly into 12 x 8-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese, eggs, white sugar and pecans together well and pour over graham cracker mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll bread out to 10 x 15-inch.
Mix butter, seasoned salt, parsley flakes and oregano.
Spread some on bread.
Cover surface with 3 1/2 ounce package sliced pepperoni.
Add cheese.
Roll up like jelly roll and spread some butter on top.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes.
Brush on remaining butter mixture after it comes out of the oven.

title: hot dill pickle
directions: Place cucumbers,
garlic,
pepper,
onion
and	dill in large mouth quart jar.
Bring to a rolling boil water, vinegar and salt. Pour over cucumbers
and seal.
Ready for use after 6 weeks.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and sugar.
Add water; stir until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Chill and serve.

title: western salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Fritos and dressing.
Add Fritos and dressing when ready to serve.

title: archibald's vidalia onion casserole
directions: Slice onions into rings and saute with butter until clear and soft.
In 9-inch casserole, layer 1/3 of soup, then onions, then cheese, making 3 layers.
Spread cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until browned.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in oil until foamy.
Mix in sugar and then remaining ingredients.
Add flour last, 1 cup at a time.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: blarney bars
directions: Mix together egg yolk, sugar, flour, baking powder, hot water and vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Put in a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot sauce
directions: Boil jalapeno peppers in water in a small saucepan until peppers soften.
Drain.
Pour whole tomatoes, jalapeno peppers, garlic salt and onion in blender until well blended.
Use for a dip with chips or top on your favorite food.
Enjoy!
Be careful, it may be hot.
If so, add more tomato.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Pour butter in large 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Layer other ingredients.
Place Saran Wrap, then aluminum foil over baking dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: green beans
directions: Cut green beans in bite size pieces; boil until tender.
Drain green beans and set aside.
Crush crackers in a paper bag with rolling pin or other utensil.
Melt butter or margarine in pan (can use same pan as the green beans).
Put crackers in melted butter or margarine and toss to warm on low heat.
Then add in the green beans and serve.

title: good cheesecake
directions: Make the cake according to directions in a big bowl.
Mix in the remaining ingredients and divide into 2 glass dishes (long), 9 x 13-inches.
First the cake mix, then cheese mix.
Makes two dishes.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown on the bottom.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Season with salt, pepper and 1 teaspoon Crisco.
Add a small amount of ketchup and boil until thick.

title: belgia beer stew
directions: Coat beef cubes in flour and brown in hot oil.
Place in an 8 to 10-quart casserole. Brown onions and garlic.
Add to casserole. Add sugar, 2 tablespoons vinegar, parsley, bay leaves, thyme, salt and pepper.
Stir. Boil the beef broth in the skillet used to brown the meat and onions.
Pour the broth over the meat mixture. Add the beer. Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Place on stove top and add remaining vinegar.
Cook until the sauce bubbles.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Pour ingredients into a blender.
Blend until smooth and ice cubes have dissolved.

title: ollie freeman's teacakes
directions: Mix together. Make out cookies. Bake at 425°.

title: noodles and cheese
directions: Cook noodles and keep them warm.
Add Parmesan cheese, Ranch dressing and sour cream to noodles and mix.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: deviled pecan balls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, then add the rest except for pecans.
Pat chopped nuts onto the outside of the balls.
Makes 2 balls.

title: bermuda fish chowder
directions: Take about 1 pound firm fresh or salt water fish fillet; cut in small bite-size pieces.
Place in a pot with 1 pound of fresh peeled tomatoes, cut in chunks.
If fresh tomatoes are not available, canned tomatoes may be used.
Add 2 small onions (halved and sliced) and 2 to 4 small white potatoes (peeled and cut in small pieces).
Flavor with thyme, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer slowly for 4 to 6 hours.
Carefully add sherry or rum pepper to taste.

title: marinade(for boneless chicken breasts)
directions: Mix all together in Ziploc bag or container.
Add 4 chicken breast halves.
Turn occasionally.
Marinate for at least 2 hours to overnight, whichever you prefer.
Best done on gas grill. Great done under broiler 10 minutes each side.

title: aunt pat's hot chicken salad
directions: Mix mayo, water and soup together.
Stir in onion, chicken, almonds, pepper, rice, salt, celery and lemon juice.
Carefully add sliced eggs.
Place all in greased casserole dish.
Top with potato chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs.
Slowly add oil, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk jello salad
directions: Bring the can of pineapple to a boil and add box of Jell-O; mix well.
Let cook and add 1 cup buttermilk and mandarin oranges with juice; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip; put in covered dish and let set overnight in refrigerator.
You may add nuts and/or miniature marshmallows.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Cook potatoes in small amount of salted water; drain and refrigerate until cool. Chop potatoes coarsely. Mix well with remaining ingredients. Bake in 1 1/2-quart dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: filled tartlets
directions: Scald milk.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Stir in eggs, cheese and seasoning.
Divide mixture between two bowls.
Add bacon to one mixture, crabmeat to the other.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange tartlet shells on greased baking sheet.
Fill 14 shells with bacon mixture and 14 with crabmeat mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 28 appetizers.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil; cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add to sugar syrup.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter and brown sugar.
Beat egg yolks; add salt, cinnamon and mace.
Mix thoroughly.
Add walnuts and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 25 minutes longer or until firm.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook all ingredients but the soda to soft ball stage, then add soda and mix well.
It will be foamy.
Pour over popcorn.

title: pam's butter cake
directions: Soften margarine in microwave; add sugar.
Add eggs.
Put extract in milk.
Add flour and milk to margarine and sugar, alternating.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with strawberries or peaches.

title: sesame shrimp and asparagus
directions: Cut asparagus into 2-inch pieces; set aside.

title: grandmother's yeast bread
directions: Yields 6 or 7 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl; dissolve and carefully add beaten eggs.
Check temperature of mixture; if warm (around 100°), then add yeast, 1/4 cup warm water and sugar which have been combined.
Beat in half the flour (whole wheat or white). Work in remainder of flour.
Turn out on board floured with white flour.
Knead at least 10 minutes (board side will be "blistered" when kneaded enough).
Let rise to almost double; bake.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix batter like pancake dough.
Melt 1/2 stick butter in baking pan.
Pour mixed batter into pan.
Spoon fruit of you choice on top of batter.
As it bakes, crust rises to the top.
Bake at 425°.
It is done when it's a golden brown.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken into melted margarine, then roll in crumb mixture.
Place in shallow pan and drizzle with remaining margarine.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: spinach and meat combination
directions: In a 3-quart pot with cover, cook beef in 1 cup water for 1/2 hour, then add chicken breast with spinach and other ingredients. Add water as needed.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Usually served over rice.
Serves 4.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into aluminum foil-lined 8 or 9-inch pan. Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off foil and then cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: ritz cracker snacks
directions: Combine dates and milk.
Cook until thick in microwave.
Cook 3 minutes; stir.
Cook 3 minutes more; stir.
Add pecans. Spread on crackers.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: sun burst stir-fry
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions; set aside. Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 c. juice
Blend
pineapple juice with 1/3 c. soy sauce, 1 Tbsp. cornstarch, pepper, garlic powder, and 1/2 c. water; set aside.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes (slice thinly).
Layer 1/2 potatoes in casserole.
Place all onion and 1/2 sauce.
Top with remaining potatoes and sauce.
Dot with butter, cover and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for an additional 35 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Dig in with raw vegetables.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Cook cranberries and 1 1/2 cups of water until popped open. Add sugar and simmer for 8 minutes.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add 2 cups cold water.
Chill until thickened.
Add cranberries, pineapple and walnuts.
Pour into greased mold.

title: champagne salad
directions: Beat creamed cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan or smaller molds.
Remove from freezer 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in glass jar.
Use 1 to 3 tsp. to cup of hot water, according to taste.

title: fruit salad medley
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans in a bowl and refrigerate.
Stir in pecans just before serving.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar.
Place everything in a glass bowl in the order given; do not stir. Should be done the day before; cover.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing with a fork.
Form into 7 or 8 thick patties.
Coat both sides with finely crushed saltine cracker crumbs on waxed paper and fry in skillet with minimum hot Crisco until lightly browned on each side.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until tender; drain.
Add soups and simmer a few minutes.
Add rice and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spring temptation pie
directions: Stir boiling water into Jell-O in medium bowl for 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Stir in sherbet; mix until melted.
Refrigerate 25 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and pineapple.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vernon's red velvet cake
directions: Prepare
cake mix per box directions.
Add food dye and paste made
from the cocoa and vinegar.
Mix well and bake as directed on cake box.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: pecan roll
directions: Mix
sugar, Karo syrup and milk together
in
saucepan. Place over lowered heat until mixture begins to
thicken.
Add vanilla. Pour
onto waxed paper and roll into a
long
roll. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and nuts, then add milk.
Mix in flours.
Drop by teaspoonful on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stuffed apples
directions: Slice apples in half.
Cut out core.
Spread the peanut butter inside and eat.

title: crab canape
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add cheese and cream.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in crabmeat, salt and pepper.
Beat egg yolk lightly with sherry and add to crab mixture.
Chill until serving time.
Just before serving, spoon into canape shells.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes until top is bubbly.

title: kids turn meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Have child do the squishing.
Have child form into a loaf and plop into a shallow baking pan.
Squirt some more ketchup on top and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes while Mom puts her feet up.
Set the table.
Don't forget the napkins.

title: beef roast
directions: Salt and pepper meat. Brown on both sides in a large skillet. While meat is browning pour beef broth in slow cooker. Reserve 2 Tbsp. broth.
Mix with cornstarch. Pour mixture and wine into slow cooker. Stir well. Add meat. Cook 7 to 8 hours on low. Use gravy over rice or potatoes.

title: sweet and sour delight
directions: Cut chicken or pork into 1/2-inch pieces.
Brown in oil; reduce heat to low.
Add onion and garlic.
Cover and cook 10 minutes. Add carrots and green pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into skillet.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serve with rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Melt shortening and cocoa together.
Add sugar to eggs and beat.
Add chocolate mixture to eggs and blend.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread in pan. Bake 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain.
Add soup, sour cream, pimentos, onion, 1/3 stuffing and water chestnuts.
Mix.
Put one third of stuffing on bottom of pan.
Pour mixture in pan. Add remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves about 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bizetti
directions: Cook beef with onions, stirring frequently. Add to remaining ingredients (EXCEPT cheese) in a large bowl. Turn into 9 x 13 pan or 3-quart casserole dish that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Top with cheese. Bake for 20 minutes in a preheated 375° oven. Serves 8 to 10. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: shrimp candelis
directions: Heat margarine and olive oil.
Add garlic which has been put through press.
Cook until garlic is cooked.
Add shrimp.
Add pepper and salt heavily as salt has to penetrate shrimp shell. When shrimp are done, add vermouth and lemon juice and cook about 2 minutes.

title: tiara cake dessert
directions: Prepare instant pudding using instructions on box, then place in refrigerator to chill.
Spray 2 fluted cake pans with Pam. Prepare cake using instructions on box and pour 1/2 of mix into each.
Bake as directed.
Allow cakes to cool before removing from pans.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Beat the three eggs in a large bowl and hot noodles, milk, cheese, salt and pepper; mix well.
Put in large casserole dish. Put butter on top in 1 teaspoon pieces.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° until brown on top, between 45 minutes and 1 hour.

title: chicken crumb parmesan
directions: In blender, combine bread, Parmesan cheese, salt and parsley.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter and pour in an oblong cake pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle nuts over the graham crumbs, then add chocolate chips, coconut and Eagle Brand milk on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes at least.

title: easy side salad
directions: Cut lettuce into salad size pieces. Cut tomatoes and toss together. Mix with Miracle Whip to desired creaminess. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° and check.
It may need to bake a little longer.

title: vanilla wafer fruitcake
directions: Place crushed vanilla wafers in large bowl.
Add chopped cherries, pineapple, pecans and raisins.
Mix well using hands. Beat eggs, sugar, milk and salt together.
Pour over fruit.
Mix well with hands.
Place in greased tube pan and press down with hand.
Wet hand before pressing, it will not stick to cake.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool 15 minutes before removing.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat broth to boiling.
Add rice and turn down heat; cover for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a small, nonstick pan or wok on medium heat, put butter or oil, carrots and onion and cook until onion is translucent.
Take out onion and carrot.
Scramble 1 egg; add onion and carrot back to egg and add cooked rice.
Cook over medium heat about 3 to 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce, if desired. Serve hot.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Empty tuna into buttered baking dish.
Add cracker crumbs. Pour egg and milk mixture over tuna and crackers.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: trifle
directions: Tear cake into bite-sized bits into 13 x 9-inch oblong pan. Mix hot water and jello; pour over cake.
Then pour pudding over cake (cherry pie filling).
Top with Cool Whip.
You can multiply this to make as much as you need.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Beat eggs, one at a time and add to the mixture.
Add vinegar, pecans, raisins and coconut. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350 degree oven.

title: hot green tomato relish
directions: Put tomatoes in large, stainless steel or crockery container with salt.

Toss well. Let stand 3 hours. Drain, but do not rinse. In large pan, put 1/2 gallon vinegar with 8 cups sugar. Heat to boiling. Add all vegetables. Return just to a boil and simmer 10 minutes only. Fill jars. Seal and process for 10 minutes in hot water bath. Do not boil (instead, bring to a good simmer; turn off heat and allow jars to sit with lids covered, for only 10 minutes).

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and simmer until sugar dissolves.

title: trailside oatmeal treats
directions: Stir flour, soda and salt together.
Set aside.
Cream margarine, peanut butter and sugars until creamy.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, then oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 42 cookies.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 325° until set.
Can be served warm or at room temperature.
Can be refrigerated.

title: mexican one dish meal
directions: Cook ground beef or turkey and onion in large nonstick skillet. Stir occasionally while cooking. When meat is lightly browned and onion is soft, drain off fat. Add all remaining ingredients except corn. Cover and simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes. Add more water if needed. Add corn; cook long enough to heat through. Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry-strawberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce.
Add Jell-O and mix.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate.

title: too easy cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
Cut crusts from bread.
Cut each slice into 5 strips. Place over fruit.
In a bowl, beat egg, flour, sugar and butter. Pour over bread.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: marion's hot poached salmon
directions: Add salt and spices to water.
Add lemon juice and onion. Bring to a boil; add salmon.
Lower the heat and poach very gentle, allowing 10 minutes per pound.

title: crunchy beef bake casserole
directions: Cook macaroni. Brown ground beef. Combine all ingredients except onions. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and put onions on and continue to bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Measure first four ingredients into sifter.
Set aside.
Rinse raisins with boiling water to plump them.
Drain.
Set aside with walnuts.

title: cream cheese pie crust
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese.
Add salt and flour. Mix with hands, refrigerate overnight.

title: black-eyed susans
directions: Mix and roll out and cut with a small biscuit cutter.
Put a date into each and fold over.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients in 2 cups water for 10 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat and add Crisco oil.
Let cool well. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian breakfast pie
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Spread rolls over pizza pan, sealing seams.
Layer sausage, potatoes and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and pepper.
Pour over pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: finger paint
directions: To 1-quart boiling water, add all other ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into jars and color with poster paint or vegetable coloring.
Use on wet shelf paper.

title: herbed bread sticks
directions: In a large bowl mix the flour, yeast, salt and herbs.
Add the olive oil and water and mix until a dough is formed.
On a floured surface knead the dough until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Place the dough in an oiled bowl, cover with a towel and set in a warm place to rise.
When the dough has doubled in size, about 30 minutes, punch it down and divide it into 16 pieces.
Roll each piece into a 12-inch "snake."

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well. Combine spinach, sour cream and onion soup.
Put in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with Pepperidge Farm crumbs (mashed until fine) with Parmesan cheese. Cook in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine soup mix with breadcrumbs.
Dip chicken in soup mixture, coating well.
Place in lightly greased large shallow baking pan; drizzle with butter.
Bake, turning once, for 10 minutes, or until tender.
Makes about 2 dozen nuggets.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour hot water on yeast cakes; let cool.
Add 2 cups flour; let rise 20 minutes.
Add eggs and the 4 cups flour (add 1 cup bran, if desired).
Mix well.
Can be refrigerated.
Take out after 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: red toy salad
directions: Place marshmallows and orange jello in bowl and pour boiling water over.
Stir until dissolved.
Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until smooth.
Add pineapple.
Then mix with the marshmallow mixture.
Whip the cup of cream and fold into mixture. Pour into 9 x 13 glass dish and chill.
When set, top with 6 ounce red jello, prepared as directed on box.
Chill until set. Cut into squares and serve.

title: eggs benedict
directions: Prepare Mock Hollandaise Sauce. Set aside. Bring 6 cups water to a boil in a large saucepan over high heat. Reduce heat to low. Carefully break 1 egg into small dish and slide egg into water. Repeat with remaining eggs. Simmer, uncovered, about 5 minutes or until yolks are just set.

title: golden rich bars
directions: In a large bowl mix cake batter, butter and 2 eggs.
Spoon into ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread evenly.
In separate bowl mix cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs until fluffy.
Pour mixture over first layer.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
The cake will look somewhat like custard.
Do not bake until firm.
Cake should be soft in the middle.
Yields 20 bars, each bar contains 192 calories (45% from fat).

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Combine butter, sugars, egg and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture; mix well. Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in upper third of oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from cookie sheets; cool on wire racks.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: texas gumdrop cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, flour, applesauce and spices, then add raisins, nuts and gumdrops.
Mix well.
Bake 2 1/2 hours in a greased and floured tube pan at 275°.
Place a pan of water under cake and steam will make it moist.
Test for doneness.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas and nuts.
Put in greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: haystacks
directions: Over low heat, melt butterscotch chips.
After melted, remove from heat and add noodles and peanuts.
Stir all together.
Then using teaspoon, scoop onto wax paper.
Cool before eating.

title: banana oatmeal bread
directions: In bowl, combine bananas, oats and milk; set aside.
In large bowl, cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine all ingredients, adding alternately with banana mixture.
Spoon into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Contains 18 slices per loaf, 180 calories a slice.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Pour into frozen pop molds, small paper cups or ice cube trays.
Insert wooden stick or spoons into paper cups or cube trays.
Freeze until firm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook onion and hamburger; add salt and pepper, bell pepper and seasoning mix, tomatoes (chopped a little), tomato sauce and chili beans.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle cheese on top with corn chips.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and water.
In another bowl, put 2 cups flour, salt and oil; mix well.
Add yeast mixture; mix.
Add 2 additional cups flour.
Add more warm water if needed to make a stiff dough.
Let rise until double.
Split dough in half.
Roll out to pan size on floured board.
Add toppings and sauce; bake at 425° until done.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, corn syrup and water in heavy pot and let come to a boil.
(Use medium heat throughout.)
Add peanuts when mixture starts to boil.
Cook until peanuts start popping and smell parched and sugar is medium brown in color, about 20 minutes. Remove from heat immediately and add baking soda.
Stir quickly. Do not beat.
Pour on a large buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool and break in small pieces.

title: tiny cream cheese biscuits
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter at medium speed of an electric mixer 2 minutes or until creamy. Gradually add flour beating at low speed just until well blended. Spoon dough into ungreased miniature 1
2/4 inch muffin pans, filling full. Bake at 400 degree for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown. Serve hot. Yields 1
1/2 dozen

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut soft butter into cake mix.
Add nuts and crumble on top of pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: german pound cake
directions: Mix butter, shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Mix at least 20 minutes until sugar is dissolved.
Blend in flour and baking powder.
Slightly warm milk and
vanilla.
Pour in and mix well. Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 8 x 14-inch pan.
Spread coconut and pecans on bottom.
Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour this mixture over pecans and coconut.
Melt butter; add softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Spread over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Chop tomato and boil eggs.
Mix everything with mayonnaise.

title: white layer cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Bake in layers at 375° for 25 minutes, in nonstick pans, or well-greased, floured pans.

title: beef and mushroom pie
directions: Fry bacon slowly in large, heavy skillet.
Remove when cooked, crumble and set aside.
Heat skillet until almost smoking, brown the beef cubes a few at a time on all sides.
Place beef and crumbled bacon in casserole and keep warm.
When all the beef has been browned, add the chopped vegetables to the skillet, reduce heat and cook until wilted.
Stir in 2 tablespoons flour, cook for a minute or two, add the wine, broth and seasonings; bring to boil, stirring to smooth out sauce.
Pour over beef, cover closely and simmer in a 325° oven about two hours or until meat is tender. Make certain it does not boil.
Remove casserole from oven and cool.
(This is best made the day before baking the pie to facilitate removal of excess fat.)

title: orange cappuccino mix
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender. Cover and blend on high for 15 seconds. Stir until well mixed. Blend for an additional 15 seconds. Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: kathleen's favorite mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil in lightly salted water just until tender.
Do not overcook.
Turn off stove.
Drain potatoes and immediately return them to the hot pot.
Set on hot stove eye that is turned off.
Pour in amount of canned milk needed for beating.
Do not disturb potatoes.
Add 1 large spoonful of mayonnaise and the butter to the undisturbed potatoes.
Let set until milk becomes lukewarm (this is important).
When milk is warm, mash potatoes slightly; add salt and pepper to taste.
Beat with an electric mixer until smooth.

title: tuna-chip casserole
directions: Combine tuna, condensed soup, peas, celery, onion, milk and Worcestershire sauce in a bowl, mixing thoroughly.
Spoon half of tuna into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with half of crushed potato chips.
Spoon remaining tuna mixture into casserole. Sprinkle with remaining potato chips.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave oven for 10 minutes at High, or until thoroughly heated. Rotate casserole one-quarter turn once.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: raisin bonbon
directions: Rinse raisins in hot water; drain. Chop raisins with food chopper or knife. Blend in peanut butter and honey. Form into 1-inch balls. Roll in nuts.

title: layered green salad
directions: Shred lettuce onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with onions, celery and water chestnuts.
Break peas apart and sprinkle over all and add shredded cheese.
Combine sugar, cheese, salt and garlic powder, mixing well.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in oil and 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
