Stir in broth and clam juice; bring to a boil.
Add the scallops, shrimp, crab and 1/8 teaspoon pepper; return to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered for 4 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink and scallops are firm and opaque, stirring gently.
Drain, reserving cooking liquid;
and set seafood mixture aside.

title: veal oscar
directions: Sprinkle veal on both sides with lemon juice, then salt and pepper.
Dust lightly with flour.
Heat butter in large skillet and saute cutlets over moderately high heat for 4 minutes on each side, until lightly browned.
Remove to a warm platter.
On each cutlet, place 4 spears of asparagus and one crab leg.
Top with Hollandaise sauce.
Serve immediately.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour.
Add oleo, then add eggs, pineapple and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice 6 large apples.
Arrange in 6 x 10-inch greased baking dish.
Mix together first 5 ingredients and spread over sliced apples.
Pour Crisco oil over all.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in 325° oven.

title: healthy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed with an electric mixer. Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add egg substitute and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and oats. Gradually add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in raisins.

title: broccoli rice salad(first place salads, 1994 rice contest)
directions: Combine bacon, broccoli, onion, raisins and rice.
Mix well. Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in a small jar.
Mix well and pour over broccoli mixture immediately before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy barbecue chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in skillet.
Place approximately a 2 pound chicken in skillet, cover and let simmer 45 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken rolls
directions: Roll chicken and cheese up in a crescent roll. Place in a cake pan. Heat soup and milk until smooth. Pour around crescents and cook in oven until crescents are brown. Sprinkle with cheese when done.

title: honey spiced peaches
directions: Combine honey, vinegar, spices and cinnamon.
Boil 10 to 12 minutes.
Strain.
Return cinnamon to spiced syrup.
Drain 1/2 of the syrup from the peaches.
Add peaches to spiced syrup and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add wine.
Store in covered glass dish in refrigerator.
Leave about a day before using.
More peaches may be added without reheating the syrup.

title: marble fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with plastic wrap.
Place corn syrup and milk in a 2-quart saucepan set on a medium-low heat burner. Add chocolate, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted, then remove from heat.
Stir in the vanilla and the sugar with a wooden spoon until the mixture is smooth.
Spread the mixture in the pan previously prepared.
Using a teaspoon, drop the peanut butter onto the fudge.
To marbleize, use a knife to swirl the peanut butter through the fudge.
Chill 2 hours or until firm. Invert onto cutting board and remove the plastic wrap.
Makes approximately 25 (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: oriental chicken and peppers
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken with soup mix, 1 tablespoon oil, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, garlic and 1 teaspoon cornstarch. Marinate 20 minutes.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O into cottage cheese.
Add drained fruit, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well and chill.

title: asparagus and chicken salad
directions: Wash and peel asparagus; cut diagonally into 1-inch pieces. Heat oil in a heavy saute pan.
When very hot, add the asparagus and stir-fry for 2 minutes, stirring constantly with a large spoon.
Add the seasoned salt, salt and pepper, stirring another 30 seconds.
Pour in chicken broth and soy sauce.
Cover; cook 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat.
Add the chicken and mix. Transfer to a serving platter.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time.
Just before serving, add the vinegar and toss until well blended.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix or sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in well-greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Frost when cool with favorite frosting.

title: eggnog bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all dry ingredients (flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg).
Combine and add to dry ingredients the beaten eggs, eggnog and vegetable oil; stir fast until combined.
Stir in the pecans and apricots.
Divide batter into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch bread pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes before removing breads to cooling rack.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, salt, milk and oleo in order and cook on top of stove in large heavy pot until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Beat the 3 egg whites and add 1 teaspoon cream of tartar and dash of salt until thick and forms peak.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Spread on top of pudding and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.
This makes a large pudding.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Makes 3/4 cup of sauce.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Pour boiling water over rhubarb to soften. Drain after 5 minutes. Mix sugar, egg and flour.
Pour over rhubarb in lower crust.
Put crisscross crust on top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan and set aside.
Beat butter and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add poppy seed filling and beat until blended.
Beat in egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating
well
after
each addition.
Add vanilla and
sour
cream and beat
just
until
blended.
Stir
flour, baking soda and salt until
mixed, add to poppy mixture gradually, beating well after each
addition.
Beat
egg
whites in separate bowl with electric mixer
until
stiff
peaks
form. Fold beaten egg whites into batter.
Spread batter evenly into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to
60 minutes
or
until
cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool
in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and
cool
completely
on
rack. Dust with confectioners sugar just before serving.
Yields 14 to 16 servings.

title: blender broccoli soup
directions: * Sour cream is for top of soup in bowl.

title: easy squash casserole
directions: Brown ground sausage.
Slice and boil the squash and onion. Combine with 1/2 cup milk into a casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots only until still a little crisp, not soft. Cook remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onion in hot shortening in saucepan.
Add mushrooms and green pepper.
Stir in the flour, salt and pepper. Combine remaining ingredients, except sour cream, and mix well to meat mixture.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender. Stir constantly, adding sour cream and heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over cooked spirelli, shell noodles or rice.

title: light yeast biscuits
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve 1 tablespoon sugar in the warm water, then add yeast.

In a large bowl, combine the remaining 1 tablespoon sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Using a pastry blender or two knives, cut butter into dry ingredients until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture to dry ingredients and stir until a soft dough forms.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead 4 minutes or until dough becomes smooth and elastic.
Place in a large bowl; spray with cooking spray, turning once to coat top of dough.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sesame-sour cream meatballs(makes 4 dozen meatballs)
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, bread crumbs, egg, milk, salt, pepper and ginger in a large bowl. Shape into 1-inch meatballs. Heat oil and butter over medium heat in skillet.
Add meatballs and brown on all sides.
Add broth. Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Prepare Sesame-Sour Cream Sauce.
Place hot meatballs in serving bowl; top with sauce.
Sprinkle with toasted sesame seed. Garnish as desired.

title: rice dish
directions: Do not stir.
Cook 35 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Combine all fruit and marshmallows; add to jello.
Chill until thickened; spread on sour cream.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Put sugar, salt, milk, margarine and peanut butter in medium saucepan and bring to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook 3 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oatmeal and almond extract.
Stir until slightly cool.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper and chill until cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add egg to milk.
Mix flour and sugar and shake with pineapple juice.
Add to milk and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Set aside to cool.
Drain fruit cocktail and mix with pineapple tidbits and marshmallows in a large bowl.
Add cooled mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: 3-step cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour mix into graham cracker crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool; refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Spread with 1 can cherry pie filling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: microwave meatball subs
directions: In large bowl, mix onion, garlic, mushrooms, ground beef, bread crumbs and basil until combined well.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on this.
Shape into 12 meatballs.

title: chili (mild)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add diced tomatoes, soup, beans, celery, onions and parsley.
Mix together.
Add chili seasoning.
Cook at least 30 minutes.

title: date dessert
directions: Beat egg
whites
stiff
and fold in all other ingredients. Bake in
square
8	or
9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fricadellen
directions: Combine beef, onion, bread, 1/2 cup of the water, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and nutmeg in large bowl; mix well.
Shape into 4 patties.
Cook patties in hot oil in large skillet until browned. Stir in gravy and 1/4 cup of water.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until cooked through.

title: carefree cranberry gelatin
directions: Drain pineapple well and reserve the juice.
Combine juice, boiling water and gelatin.
Chill slightly.
Combine in pineapple, sour cream and cranberry sauce.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: chocolate-coconut rice squares
directions: Combine water, sugar and salt in medium saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add chips and coconut to hot rice and stir until chips are melted.
Cover and chill.
Fold whipped topping into rice mixture.
Pour into waxed paper-lined 8-inch square pan or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover and chill until firm, about 1 hour. Remove paper and cut into squares.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with noodles and bake 30 minutes longer.
Bake at 350°.

title: stuffed crabby eggs
directions: Shred crab meat.
Discard any shell.
Cut peeled eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash or put through ricer.
Add rest of ingredients to taste, except paprika, and mix well.
Stuff each egg half with mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled before serving.
Can substitute shredded shrimp.

title: pink arctic freeze
directions: Cream the sugar with cream cheese.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Fold in cranberry sauce, pineapple, nuts and whipped cream.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and freeze. Cut in slices, then squares to serve.

title: crispy oven-fried chicken
directions: You will need nonstick cooking spray.

title: sicilian baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in a large baking pan.
Peel and cut potatoes in quarters lengthwise.
Cut quarters in half again.
Place potatoes in between chicken.
Sprinkle herbs over all.
Slice onion and place on top of potatoes and chicken.
Drizzle the oil on top. Bake for 1 hour at 375°, turning chicken and potatoes after first 1/2 hour.

title: cream cheese potato soup(ready in 1 hour or less.)
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine the water and boillion. Add the cream cheese; cook and stir until cheese is melted. Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered for 18-20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat
oven
Sift together first 6 ingredients. Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in bowl.
Add dry ingredients
and
butter.
Mix
only until flour is moistened. Stir in nuts.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse broccoli to thaw.
Drain well. Mix together all ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes in a greased preheated cast-iron skillet.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, zucchini, sugar and vanilla. Mix well.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, baking powder and pecans.
Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in 2 greased loaf pans.

title: lemon whippersnappers
directions: Combine cake mix, Cool Whip and egg and stir well.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar; roll to coat.
Place 1 to 1 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Makes several dozen.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and flavoring of your choice.
At this point, you can add a few drops of food coloring if you plan to use one color for the whole batch.
Gradually add 2 to 2 1/2 cups powdered sugar.
Knead until no longer sticky.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls. Roll in sugar.
Flatten balls with a fork.
Let dry at room temperature.
Store loosely covered, in the refrigerator.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: mother's chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together until well beaten.
Pour into oiled pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: party chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients and add mayonnaise and sour cream. Mix thoroughly and chill. Serves 10 to 12.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix Dream Whip by instructions on package; set aside.
Cream sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Combine with Dream Whip.
Mix melted margarine with cracker crumbs.
Alternate layers, starting with crumbs, then pie filling, then cheese mixture.

title: skinny minnies
directions: Blend all together.
Roll into 25 balls.
Roll in sugar. Press with fork to flatten.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350°
for 10 minutes.

title: garlic and herb vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms; add soup, cheese and broccoli in a casserole dish.
Top mixture with crumbled toast and sprinkle with butter.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy onion stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
Remove stems from mushrooms; discard stems.
Fill caps with whipped cream cheese; broil 5 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: veggie appetizer
directions: Pat out crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan to make crust.
Bake as directed; let cool.
Top with room temperature cream cheese, buttermilk dressing and dill weed.
Spread over cooled crescent rolls.
Top with chopped vegetables, then grated cheese.
Chill 1 hour.
Serves 24.

title: carrots vichy
directions: Combine water, butter, salt, nutmeg, pepper and sugar with carrots.
Simmer, covered, 8 to 10 minutes, or until tender-crisp. Stir in lemon juice and parsley before serving.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the hot water.
Mix milk, Miracle Whip, jello, hot water and vinegar and refrigerate.
When it is set to the consistency of egg white, add the remaining ingredients.

title: pommes frites
directions: In a heavy, deep pot or an electric fryer, heat the oil to 360°. Add the potatoes in batches and fry until golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes per batch. Drain on paper towels and season with salt and pepper. Makes 4 servings.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Add sauce mix to meat.
Cook spaghetti or noodles until done.
Mix all together and season to taste.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar with flour.
Add egg yolks and sweet milk. Add butter.
Cook until thick and put in vanilla.
Put mixture into 8-inch baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: foul salad (fava bean)
directions: Drain the foul, wash it and put in a small pan.
Add salt, 1 cup of water and let cook until it boils.
Pour mixture into bowl, add lemon juice, onion, parlsey and oil.
Mix well.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Combine margarine and stuffing mix.
Spread 3/4 of stuffing mix in casserole dish.
Layer chicken over stuffing mix.
Pour 1 cup chicken broth and cream of chicken soup over that.
Sprinkle rest of stuffing mix over all.
Pour 1/2 cup chicken broth over stuffing mix.

title: cucumber cream cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add next four ingredients and mix well.
Stir in onion and cucumber.
Put in covered container.
Chill one hour before serving. Serve with crackers.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Measure sifted flour; add soda and salt.
Sift again.
Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Fold into batter.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Put a little grease in bottom of skillet and cook meat and onions until real brown.
Add salt and pepper.
Add chili powder, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste.

title: meat vegetable loaf(low calorie)
directions: Mix ingredients lightly in a bowl.
Shape into a loaf in greased, shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar in medium bowl.
Cut in butter to make crumb mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside 3/4 cup mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, pumpkin, eggs, cinnamon, allspice and vanilla in a large mixer bowl.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over baked crust. Sprinkle with reserved topping.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting into bars.

title: foundation sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast	and
1	tablespoon
sugar
in
lukewarm water. Scald
milk;
add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add 2
cups
flour to make a batter.
Add yeast and beaten eggs, beat well.	Add remaining flour or enough to make a soft dough. Knead lightly and place in greased bowl.
Cover and set in	warm place,
free
from	draft.	Let
rise
until doubled in bulk, about 2 hours.
When light, punch dough down and shape as desired. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Press into pan flour, powdered sugar and butter and bake in 350° oven 15 minutes in glass pan in oven at 325°.
Mix very well eggs, sugar and salt.
Add rhubarb to mixture.
Spread over top of crust and bake in 350° oven 35 minutes.
A double recipe fits in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mixture is single recipe.

title: meat pies
directions: Brown pine nuts in butter till lightly browned.
Remove from pan and brown gd. chuck in butter with onion, seasoning and juice. Add pine nuts. Cool.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Shape bread dough into balls, 6-8 inch diameter circles.
Fill with meat mixture and fold dough over meat into a rectangle shape.
Pinch seams together. Brush bottom of a 2 inch jelly roll pan with melted rendered butter (no salt). Place meat pies on tray and bake 20 mins on bottom rack until golden brown.
Raise to top rack to lightly brown.
Remove from tray and brush with butter from tray.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine cake and pudding mixes.
Add eggs, oil, orange juice, Galliano and vodka.
Beat on low speed of mixer for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed for 5 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove to rack and pour glaze over cake while still warm.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Mix and add to first mixture.
Stir once daily for 6 to 8 days. This will keep up to 1 year.

title: fauschnaught's(mom-mom's)
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1 cup lukewarm water. Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix flour, salt, sugar and Crisco fine like pie dough.
Beat eggs.
Add 2 cups warm water.
Add to flour mix. Add yeast mix last.
Work dough lightly 10 minutes.
Add flour as needed.
Cover and let rise.
When doubled in size, roll out dough, cut donuts and let them rise until doubled.
Deep fry to golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Coat with 10x sugar by shaking in paper bag.

title: coconut icing
directions: While cake layers are baking, put into mixing bowl the sour cream, sugar and coconut.
Heat in a saucepan 1 cup milk and 1 cup sugar.
To this, add one of the packages of coconut.
Bring to a boil.
When cake is cool, spread milk and coconut between the layers.
Let the layers set before placing coconut and sour cream between the layers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 3 to 4 minutes. Drain.
Mix all ingredients except broccoli in a casserole.
Place the drained broccoli in the mixture.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Add other ingredients. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° or put in crock-pot on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Mix sugar with flour and salt; stir in milk until smooth.
Add beaten egg yolks, lemon juice and rinds. Beat egg whites. Fold into mixture. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350°.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Arrange skin side up in baking dish.
In a bowl, mix butter, pineapple, syrup, lemon juice, soy sauce, ginger, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spoon over chicken. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, basting frequently with sauce.

title: cranberry-mustard turkey tenderloins(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9-inch square or 9 x 11-inch baking pan, arrange turkey tenderloins.
In small bowl, combine mustard and 1 teaspoon brown sugar; spread evenly over turkey.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes.

title: chow chow
directions: Finely chop onions and peppers. Mix all vegetables with salt. Let stand overnight. Drain well. Tie mixed spices in bag. Add sugar and spices to vinegar and simmer 20 minutes. Add other ingredients; simmer until hot. Remove spice bag. Put chow chow into hot jars and seal at once.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place the sliced apples in a greased baking dish.
Cover with a mixture of the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg.
Pour the melted and cooled shortening over all.
Sprinkle with the cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until apples are done.
Good served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixer.
Blend well.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 60 to 90 minutes.

title: white frosting
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to boil until hard ball stage. Slowly add to beaten egg whites (soft peaks).
Continue beating until stiff, then add vanilla and powdered sugar.
Beat until blended.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until almost done and drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients and put in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle the top with corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine yolks, sugar and lime juice in stainless steel bowl. Mix with wire whisk. Place bowl over a sauce pan of boiling water and whisk constantly until thickened. Remove bowl and mix in condensed milk. Pour into pie crust. Bake 30 minutes.

title: crunchies
directions: Cream together the fat, sugar and syrup.
Add flour, oatmeal, baking powder and a few drops of vanilla.
Knead until the mixture binds.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick; cut into rounds or fingers. Bake in moderate oven until golden brown, for about 20 minutes. These biscuits keep well stored in airtight tins.
(GE)

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix; spread evenly in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed. Serve with large tortilla chips.
Yields 6 cups.

title: cake like banana bread
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda. Blend in the shortening, bananas and eggs or egg whites.
Fold together quickly and do not overmix. Spoon or pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Loosen edges and cool on rack or cool completely in pan. Glaze with confectioners sugar and water mix.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.

title: spaghetti with beef and mushroom stir-fry
directions: Combine soy sauce, oil, garlic and ginger in a mixing bowl. Add beef strips and toss well to coat.
Cover and marinate for 1 hour.
In wok or skillet, heat 4 tablespoons oil.
Add beef mixture and broccoli; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add onions, pepper strips and mushrooms; stir-fry until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Blend water, cornstarch, bouillon and salt; stir into beef mixture.
Cook until thickened; keep warm.
Prepare spaghetti as directed and drain.
Add beef mixture and toss to mix.
Serve with soy sauce, if desired.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake your empty pie crust in oven.
Let it cool.
Cut bananas in slices.
Dip in lemon juice to avoid browning and line the bottom of pie crust with them.
Cut up your washed strawberries and mix with a strawberry glaze (you can find this in the produce department of your grocery store).
Pour a huge amount over the bananas.
Then mix some whole washed strawberries with glaze and stick them all over the pie.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: parmesan baked chicken
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Beat together milk and egg. Roll chicken in egg mixture.
Then roll in potato flake mixture. Melt a stick of margarine in a casserole dish.
Place chicken in the dish and roll in margarine.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until juices run clear and chicken is golden brown.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Let simmer 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate cool bars
directions: Combine crumbs and melted butter. Press firmly into bottom of 9-inch square pan. Grate or finely chop 1/2 package of the chocolate. Set aside. Heat remaining chocolate and milk in medium saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted. With whisk, beat in cream cheese until smooth. Cool 5 minutes. Fold in 3 1/2 cups of whipped topping and the grated chocolate. Spread mixture over crumbs. Spread remaining whipped topping over chocolate layer. Freeze until firm, about 2 hours. Garnish as desired. Cut into bars. Makes about 15.

title: fruited chicken in cream
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken breast halves in dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain off excess liquid.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well. Spoon over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: low cholesterol breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Spread over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Beat together milk, egg substitute and margarine.
Pour over sausage.
Layer hash browns and Cheddar cheese.
Bake 1 hour.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken on low till tender.
Mix soup, sour cream, 1/3 of crumbs, 1/3 of poppy seed in casserole dish.
Add chicken.
Top with crumbs and poppy seed.
Bake at 350 til bubbly and light brown.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together at low speed, then blend together at high speed with eggs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: rice casserole(great with beef.)
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish. Add both cans of soup.
Stir in rice. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken with wine sauce
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with mixture. Shake off and reserve excess flour.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in large skillet over medium heat.
Brown chicken; remove from skillet.
Add remaining margarine, mushrooms, onion and 2 tablespoons chopped parsley.
Saute until onion is transparent. Remove from heat.
Stir in reserved flour.
Blend in wine.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Add chicken.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.
Garnish with remaining parsley.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread in small casserole dish. Bake covered at 350° for 35 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Place bread on top and broil uncovered until the bread is browned.
Serve immediately so the bread doesn't get soggy.

title: shrimp singapore
directions: In skillet, cook onions and garlic in butter for 2 minutes. Stir in soy sauce and salt.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice noodles.
Mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with rice noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spanish noodles
directions: In frying pan with cover, melt shortening.
Add meat and cook until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and steam until noodles are tender.
Takes about 20 minutes.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain.
Add water and seasoning from soup, stir.
Add cabbage and cover, cook on low heat about one minute.
`Boil water in saucepan.
Add broken noodles from soup. Cook about 1 minute then drain water.
Add cooked noodles to cabbage and meat mixture.
Stir, cover and cook on low heat about 1 minute.
Cabbage should be slightly crunchy.

title: kraft macaroni dinner
directions: Cook dinner. Add cheese packet, milk, eggs, onions, ham, parsley and soup. Mix well. Put in casserole dish. Top with Swiss cheese. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: potato bread
directions: Cook 1 medium potato in 2 1/2 cups water for 15 minutes. Reserve the water.
Mash the potato (should be 1 cup).
In a large bowl, sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup reserved potato water that has been cooled to 105° to 115°.
To remaining potato liquid, add water (if necessary) to make 2 cups.
Add salt, sugar, oleo and 1 cup mashed potatoes.
To yeast mixture, add mashed potato liquid and 3 1/2 cups flour.
Beat with a mixer until smooth (2 minutes). Gradually add 3 1/2 cups additional flour, mixing with hands until dough is smooth and stiff (leaves side of bowl).
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Let rise until doubled (1 hour) covered.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar until thickened.
Add salt, warm milk and vanilla.
Pour this mixture over the dried bread that has been crumbled up and placed in a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and raisins, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until thick in the middle.
Serve with the Vanilla Sauce as a topping.

title: montana swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into 6 serving size pieces.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and chili powder; pound 2 tablespoons of mixture into meat. Heat shortening in 10-inch skillet; brown meat on both sides. Drain excess fat from skillet.
Add undrained tomatoes, onion, celery, carrot, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Cover.
Simmer for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove meat; place on a warm serving plate.
Skim excess fat off sauce.
Combine 1/4 cup water with remaining flour mixture and stir into sauce.
Cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
Serve meat and sauce over hot cooked rice or noodles. Makes 6 servings.

title: easy caramel popcorn
directions: In large shallow roasting pan place popcorn and nuts.
Place in 250° oven while preparing glaze.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan stir brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine and salt.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat.
Without stirring, boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over warm popcorn and nuts.
Stir to coat well.
Bake in 250° oven, stirring constantly, 1 hour.
Cool; break apart.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: crockpot dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients well. Put in crock pot and cook on low for 3 hours or high for 2 hours.

title: french apple pie
directions: Arrange half of apples in pastry-lined pie pan.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, flour, raisins and lemon juice; sprinkle half of mixture over apples.
Add remaining apples.
Sprinkle with remaining mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Place top crust on pie. Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: congealed chicken salad
directions: Combine soup and cheese.
Melt in double boiler or microwave. Mix gelatin with water.
Add to soup mixture.
Add Miracle Whip. Add rest of ingredients.
Put in 7 x 12-inch dish and refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: creamed chicken paprika(tejfeles csirke paprikas)
directions: Cut chicken into sections.
Brown onion in fat in large pot, add washed chicken, salt, paprika and water.
Simmer until chicken is tender. Mix flour with sour cream until smooth, in separate bowl.
Add to chicken before serving.
Serve with dumplings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip cream; when it peaks, add yogurt and fresh (washed and drained) raspberries.
Goes great with fresh strawberries, bananas, apple, melon, marshmallows, etc.

title: nachos supreme
directions: Prepare ground beef with taco seasoning according to package directions.

If you are using a regular onion, fry with the beef. Spread beans in a thin layer in the bottom of a 12-inch pizza pan. Next layer the taco mixture, green chilies, green onions, taco sauce and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and edge is bubbly.
Serve with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Bring water and butter to slow boil.
Place scallops and dressing in the baking dish.
Add the boiling water.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes with an aluminum foil cover.
Take cover off for another 10 minutes.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Toss together zucchini and salt.
Leave set to drain for 15 minutes, then add beaten egg, onion and flour.
Pepper to taste. Drop by tablespoon into skillet with melted butter.
Brown on both sides.

title: chicken simon and garfunkel(seasoned with parsley, sage, rosemary and thyme, of course!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound each chicken breast until thin. Brush liberally with butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Lay each chicken breast on a slice of cheese and roll up, fastening with a toothpick.
Combine the beaten egg with water. Roll the chicken in the flour, egg mixture and crumbs. Evenly space in a baking pan. Combine the melted butter with the parsley, sage, rosemary and thyme.
Drizzle the herbed butter over the chicken rolls.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Pour the sherry over the chicken and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: four-layer delight
directions: Crust:
Mix together first 3 ingredients. Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and brown.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apple, celery, nuts and mayo; toss.
If desired, mound salad in lettuce cups and garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: cheesy veggies
directions: Put veggies in butter lined casserole.
Melt together Velveeta and 1/2 stick of margarine.
Pour over cooked and drained veggies. Smash 32 Ritz crackers with 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Put on top of veggies and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks for about 1 minute or until frothy and a deep lemon
color.
Add
can
of milk and beat	for
another minute. Keeping
beaters
going,
slowly
add
lime
juice. Mixture will thicken immediately, beat until well combined and smooth.
Turn filling into cooled pie crust and chill
for
at least 4 hours. Add whipped cream and serve.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix oranges, almonds, lettuce and onion. Mix dressing ingredients and toss with salad. (Fresh strawberries can be used in season.)

title: barbara's gourmet potatoes
directions: Over low heat, melt butter.
Add cheese; let melt.
Add sour cream, green onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes.
Grease a 2-quart casserole and add potato mixture.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: five layer dinner (diabetic)
directions: In a casserole dish, layer the ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Boil rice in a little less water than you normally would the night before you will fry it.
Refrigerate.

title: crunchy ham casserole
directions: Cook broccoli spears for 3 minutes. Drain. Set aside. Cook macaroni. Combine macaroni and ham in 3-quart casserole. Blend soup, sour cream and milk. Pour half of the mixture over ham and macaroni. Arrange broccoli on top. Pour remaining soup mixture over macaroni and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with crushed French fried onions. Bake 5 minutes more.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Stir hot water, margarine and contents of vegetable/seasoning packet in bowl until margarine is melted.
Add stuffing crumbs and egg; stir until moistened.
Spoon stuffing onto each chicken breast; wrap chicken around stuffing.
Place seam side down, in greased shallow baking dish.
Brush with melted margarine.
Place any remaining stuffing in center of dish.
Bake 30 or 35 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Heat soup, water and dill in a saucepan.
Serve over chicken.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil the chicken (2 to 3 cups water).
Bone it.
Save the broth.
Cook onion, celery and carrot in chicken broth along with rice.
Cook until rice is tender.
Add 1/2 cup mushroom soup and the mushrooms.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Watch for dryness.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese and peppermint extract.
Add powdered sugar until smooth.
Knead in the food coloring.
Form into small balls.
Dip into the sugar.
Press with glass (one with a design on the bottom).
Dry (let dry overnight).

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together; cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and bananas, beating until light. Alternately add flour mixture and milk.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until done.
Remove pan; cool on rack and store overnight before slicing.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly sugar, shortening and egg. Stir in milk.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir.
Blend in berries.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with crumb topping.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Add 2 cups boiling water to jello.
Stir in pie filling and pineapple with juice and some pecans, if desired.
Pour in oblong dish; cover and let congeal overnight.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, curry powder and soy sauce together.
Mix into remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate and let stand for several hours.
Serves 12.

title: salisbury venison steak
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 10 ingredients
Mix well. Shape into 10 patties; thoroughly coat each patty with flour. Heat 1/3 cup oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add patties and brown on both sides.
Transfer patties to a greased roasting pan. Place onion and mushrooms over meat.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients above.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashion cocoa fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, mix cocoa and sugar; add canned milk and mix well.
Over low heat, bring mixture to boil; lower heat and continue cooking to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, butter and nuts.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Beat mixture until it starts to lose its shine.
Pour quickly into buttered 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Cool part way in fridge; cut into squares and return to fridge until completely cool.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Blend tomatoes and soup until smooth.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 of each of the chicken, tortillas, onion, soup-tomato mixture and cheese.
Repeat a second layer, ending with cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, or until bubbly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: deluxe corn bread
directions: Beat eggs, then mix in sour cream, oil and corn.
Add cornmeal.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 375°. Can be doubled for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
This makes a lot!
You can half with a friend or give as gifts.
Add boiling water.

title: jacob's pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter and a little more milk and flour gradually. Add vanilla. Bake in cold oven at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes to 2 hours.

title: fae's kwik-n-easy party dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with assorted vegetable dippers.

title: baked asparagus
directions: Drain liquid off asparagus. Add juice to mushroom soup, chopped pimientos and chopped mushrooms in a saucepan. Cook over low heat to pouring consistency. Place in layers in greased casserole, starting with 1/2 the asparagus, egg slices, cheese, cracker crumbs and soup mixture; repeat, ending with grated cheese. Garnish with paprika. Bake until thick and bubbly at 300°.

title: lemon carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until tender-crisp.
Drain.
In saucepan, mix sugar, lemon juice and butter.
Heat until boiling. Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add carrots and coat well.
Serve warm.

title: crawfish iberia
directions: Saute onions in butter until clear.
Add crawfish and saute for 3 minutes.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Add milk; simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked spinach.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: green chili cheese casserole
directions: Place peppers, cut and seeded, in buttered casserole dish. Add grated cheese.
In another dish, beat eggs.
Add milk gradually to eggs, Bisquick and salt.
Pour this over cheese and peppers.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: super duper bean pot
directions: Place all beans in casserole.
Brown garlic and onion in grease.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, spices and dash of salt; mix with apples.
Fill pie shell with apple mixture.
Dot with butter. Adjust top crust, cutting slits for escape of steam.
Seal and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, beating well.
Add as much flour as can be worked in with a spoon.
Roll the dough out thin as tissue paper.
Let dry on one side, then turn to dry on the other side.
Use a noodle cutter to cut noodles.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour and seasonings; roll meat in mixture.
Preheat electric frypan or skillet to 340° or hot.
Add fat; when melted, add meat.
Brown, turning to brown all sides.
Add onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Saute until partially tender.
Add liquid, all sauces and green pepper.
When boiling, turn down to simmer.

title: pansy's raw apple cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together by hand, adding apples and nuts last.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry patch punch
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a blender. Whirl to consistency of thick slush. Place 2 ice cubes in each glass. Fill 3/4 full of fruit slush. Fill remainder with ginger ale or 7-Up. Serves 4.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together shortening, sugar, eggs, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crumbs with 1 stick melted butter and put in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Next, beat eggs, 2 sticks butter and powdered sugar for 13 minutes at high speed and put on top of crumbs.
Put a layer of sliced bananas and a layer of pineapple. Top with thawed Cool Whip and garnish with cherries and pecans.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except marshmallow cream.
Bake in greased pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
When removed from oven, spread marshmallow cream on top while hot.
Top with icing.

title: sweet and sour beef
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Remove and set aside.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch in skillet.
Add vinegar, soy sauce and juice from canned pineapple.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened. Add pineapple chunks and meat.
Simmer until 5 minutes before serving time.
If necessary, add water, pineapple juice or apple juice to thin the sauce.
Five minutes before serving time, stir in carrots and green pepper.

title: orange baked pork chops
directions: Cut fat from chops. Place in shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over pork chops.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: teenagers favorite taco casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook ground beef and onions until beef is browned and onion is tender; drain.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch dish, spread refried beans; sprinkle beef mixture over beans.
Add layers of olives (reserving some for garnish), green chilies and cheese.
Spread taco sauce over all.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana homemade ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Stir in 4 mashed bananas.
You can substitute strawberries or peaches for the bananas.
Freeze. Yield:
5 quarts.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon slowly.
Drain.
Saute onion in fat.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Cook until smooth and bubbly.
Add vinegar and water.
Stir and boil for 1 minute.
Add potatoes and bacon.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: randy's favorite
directions: Slice bananas and arrange on plate.
Microwave peanut butter for 30 to 45 seconds.
Pour over banana slices.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Serve while still warm.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Sprinkle and mix with flour (about 1/4 cup); stir in milk to make gravy.
Cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and cocoa; stir well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and stir well after each addition.
(Do not beat.)
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes. Test center with a toothpick.
If it comes out clean, it's done.

title: perfect pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, milk, eggs, and oil.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in grated german chocolate bar. Pour into greased and floured baking pan and bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain and add other ingredients.
Bake in glass baking dish until bubbly and slightly brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: chocolate custard(for 2 pies)
directions: Makes 2 pies.
Have pie crust already cooked and cooled.

title: okie corn
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter. Mix the cream-style corn, whole kernel corn, butter, eggs, onion and green pepper with cornbread mix. Bake in a greased 9 x 13 pan 25 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven. Add on top the sour cream and cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: homemade hamburger helper
directions: Brown hamburger meat in a large skillet; drain meat and return to skillet.
Add macaroni and cheese and water.
Simmer until macaroni is tender.
More cheese may be added for cheesier flavor.

title: walnut beer bread(makes two loaves)
directions: Heat beer to 105° to 115° and pour 1/2 cup into a small bowl. Stir in the yeast and let stand 10 minutes.
Mix the flours, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Pour yeast mixture, oil and remaining 1 cup beer into the well and stir until blended.
Knead dough on a floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes, adding more flour if necessary.
Grease large bowl with walnut oil.
Cover with damp towel and let rise until double.
May also let rise in fridge overnight.

title: dr. pepper icing
directions: Heat margarine, Dr. Pepper and cocoa until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients. If necessary, add more powdered sugar or a small amount of margarine until of the proper spreading consistency. Frost cake.

title: johnnie mac casserole
directions: Boil macaroni according to package directions.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add Sloppy Joe mix, tomato paste or sauce (according to directions).
Mix drained macaroni, hamburger mixture and corn.
Use half of cheese in mixture.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Crumble the hash browns into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine
1/2 cup melted margarine, cream of chicken soup, sour cream,
salt
and
onion;
spread
over
hash browns.
Cut the cheese
into
cubes
and spread over the top of the casserole. Sprinkle
the corn flakes over top.
Drizzle the remaining 1/4 cup margarine over all.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: appleberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen berries.
Stir until fruit is thawed.
Add applesauce and mix well.
Pour into serving dishes.
Chill until firm.

title: easy hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add soups and sour cream and simmer for a few minutes. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: rotel dip
directions: Melt cheese in pan.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Brown hamburger and then add to cheese mix.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: 6 month slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion and sweet pepper and add salt.
Mix and let stand 10 minutes.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Add seasonings.
Spoon into a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cut biscuits into halves. Place cut side down around edges and over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in large baking dish (13 x 9) sprayed with Pam. Mix soup, broth and rice. Pour over the pork chops. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pecan ice cream
directions: Mix all together; add enough milk to fill freezer.

title: sour cream
directions: Mix in blender.
This makes a perfect sour cream that can be used in any recipe calling for sour cream.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Lightly oil a heavy skillet over high heat and brown the meat. Add the onion and peppers and cook until tender, about 4 minutes. In large mixing bowl, combine the cornmeal, milk, creamed corn, eggs, bacon fat and soda.
Mix thoroughly.

title: emerald squares
directions: Bottom Layer:
Combine 1/2 cup butter and cocoa in saucepan over low heat.
Stir until well blended.
Remove from heat; add 1/2 cup sugar, egg and vanilla. Stir in crumbs.
Mix well and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna, chop eggs and mix it all together.
Chill and serve on crackers or in a sandwich for school!
Enjoy!!!

title: mother's cobbler
directions: Melt the margarine in sheath cake pan.
Sift the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix with the milk and pour over butter. Add fruit, cinnamon and more sugar.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Lower heat to 350° and cook until done.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Melt butter; beat in egg well.
Add yogurt, soda, baking powder and sugar.
Fold in flour.
Pour in cupcake holders and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils and sugar is completely dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until temperature reaches 260°.
After boiling has ceased, stir in flavoring and coloring.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let stand until cool enough to handle.
Grease hands and pull until it has a satin like finish and light color.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Wrap in waxed paper.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.
Add pineapple; fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze until firm.
If kept in freezer, good as long as lasts.

title: easy layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven, then add graham cracker crumbs.
Press down.
Put coconut and chips in pan.
Drizzle milk over all.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool completely and cut.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta following package directions and drain well.
Mix in pepper, onion, olives, artichokes and nuts.
Toss together and set aside.

title: diet 3 bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Toss, cover and chill. Serve with slotted spoon.
One-half cup serving equals 1/2 vegetable, 1/2 bread or 1/2 protein; 10 optional calories.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Combine next three ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted, then add broccoli.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Combine Bisquick mix and sugar.
Blend eggs and milk with shortening and vanilla.
Add liquid all at once to dry ingredients. Mix only until dampened.
Pour into greased wax paper lined 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Peel apples and slice thin.
Place over top of batter in pan.

title: red cabbage salad
directions: Toss sliced apples with lemon juice.
Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: meat dish
directions: Add onion, green pepper and celery to spaghetti and meat; salt and pepper.
Put in baking dish.
Pour over all the tomato sauce or tomato juice.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 3 tablespoons syrup.
Combine ingredients, except pecans.
Form into ball.
Top with chopped pecans.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer water, coffee and sugar for 2 hours.
Cool and add vanilla and vodka.
Let stand 3 to 4 weeks.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Drain oil from tuna and put tuna in a small bowl.
Break bread into small piece, add to tuna.
Add all other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into cakes, fry in hot oil until brown.

title: tang drink
directions: Dissolve- drink mix in pineapple juice in pitcher or punch bowl.
Stir in ginger ale and add ice cubes. Garnish with orange slices.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Cut a 1/2-inch strip of peel from around the middle of each potato.
Place potatoes in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add water. Cover with lid and cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes and stir in parsley, butter, salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Brown meat and onions in margarine.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Layer on bottom of Pyrex dish. Layer sliced raw potatoes over all chops, to the top of dish. Pour 1 jar Heinz chili sauce over potatoes.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil.
Top with 1 package frozen peas.
Bake 20 minutes longer. May be doubled in a larger dish.

title: country style cabbage
directions: Cook ham with some water until tender.
Put cabbage and potatoes with the ham; cook for 30 minutes.
Take up and drain. Cut cabbage as small as you want.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Mix ingredients and put in double boiler.
Mix with electric mixer while cooking until it forms peaks or is at spreading consistency.

title: peach ice cream
directions: With electric mixer, beat eggs; add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add Eagle Brand and vanilla; beat well.
Add peaches and milk.
Freeze as usual in ice cream freezer.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: In skillet, cook until brown the brown sugar, shortening and cream.
Add milk, flour and egg yolk.
Continue cooking until thickened.
Pour into pie pastry and cool.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in mixing bowl and mix until smooth. Stir in flour, one cup at a time until thoroughly mixed.
Mix in nuts.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Drop from soup spoon onto cookie sheet.
Cook at 300° until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first three ingredients together to form a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and refrigerate.

title: swiss-gruyere fondue
directions: Toss together cheeses, flour, mustard and garlic powder.
In a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, microcook the wine, Worcestershire sauce and 1/4 cup water, uncovered, on 100% power (High) 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until hot.
Add cheese mixture to hot liquid.
Microcook, uncovered, on 50% power (Medium) for 8 to 9 minutes, or until cheese is melted, stirring every 2 minutes. Serve with bread cubes.
Reheat as necessary in the casserole on 50% power (Medium) for 3 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Slice Polish sausage into 1/2 in pieces.
Drain and rinse sauerkraut.

title: cornish game hens
directions: Thaw, wash and remove giblets from hens.
Rub salt all over inside and out.
Sprinkle with tenderizer.
Place in roasting pan, breast side up.
Bake at 425° about 1 hour or until brown and very tender.
Baste with liquid several times during cooking to keep moist.
(To keep more juicy, bake breast down and turn last 15 minutes to brown.
It's more trouble, but worth it.)
Serve with wild rice and English peas.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugars.
Add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill dough 1 hour or overnight.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Press with small glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs, onions and mushrooms.
Heat soup before pouring over top.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
If refrigerated before baking, bake for 1 hour.
Bake uncovered.

title: mrs. whitten's happi time punch
directions: Use green food coloring and red cherries for a festive air.

title: bill's fried catfish
directions: Wash fillets in lemon or lime juice.
Place on paper towel to dry at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Salt to your taste, using a mixture of garlic salt, cayenne, black pepper, chili powder and red pepper.

title: microwave sliced bake potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but
not
all
the way through.
Put in microwave-safe dish
and sprinkle with melted butter and parsley.
Microwave on
High power 10 minutes; rearrange potatoes after 5 minutes. Let
rest
for
5 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar and Parmesan cheese.
Microwave
4 to
6 minutes on High until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft.

title: momma's coffee cake
directions: Melt 1/2 of butter with brown sugar and pour into Bundt pan. Top with nuts and cherries.

title: african rice dishes
directions: Wilt greens in hot oil.
Do not brown.
Add water to cover. Cook rice according to the directions on box.
Set aside, keeping rice hot.
Add 2 tablespoons tomato paste.
Add 3 or 4 beef bouillon cubes, crushed.
Add meat, halfway cooked.
Simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Serve over hot rice.

title: darlene's delight
directions: Mix butter and graham crackers and pat down in bottom of cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/4 cup milk.
Pour over graham crackers.
Mix pudding and pour over sugar mixture. Top with Cool Whip.

title: sunday chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine. Heat broth and undiluted soups and pour over cornbread crumbs. Add onion and celery. Mix well. Season with salt and pepper. Pour half of dressing mixture in greased deep 3-quart casserole. Add chicken and top with rest of dressing. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Serves 6.

title: baby food cake
directions: Separate egg whites; beat until stiff.
Beat egg yolks (yellows).
Blend egg whites and egg yolks with oil.
Mix flour and other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: cream of tomato soup(yields 4 servings)
directions: Cook tomatoes, onion, pepper, cayenne, sugar and bay leaf together for 15 minutes; strain.
Melt butter and blend in flour. Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Garnish with watercress.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs; mix sugar and flour together to keep down lumps. Add sugar and flour mixture to well beaten eggs.
Add pineapple juice and butter.
Cook to a cream sauce.
Pour over pineapple and bake at 300° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until slightly brown on top.

title: fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 275° (slow).
Line two loaf pans with brown paper. Mix oil, sugar, molasses and eggs.
Beat vigorously with spoon or mixer two minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding
and pineapple; add Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: beef stroganoff skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender.
Drain fat from beef.
Blend in mushroom soup and sour cream; add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Cook 10 minutes or until noodles are done.
Stir often.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: vegetables in cheese sauce(melts in your mouth.)
directions: In a 3-quart microwave-safe casserole dish, stir soup until smooth.
Stir in milk, basil and garlic.
Mix well.
Add cauliflower, onion and peas.
Stir to coat well.
Cover with lid. Microwave on High 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring twice during cooking.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: mary's devil's food cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and cream until light.
Add chocolate and mix well.
Sift together flour and soda Add flour and sour cream alternately, ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake.
Mix as directed for 2 (9 inch) layers.
Cool and slice into 4 layers.

title: creamed onions
directions: Cook onions in boiling salted water 20 minutes if using fresh onions.
Drain onions; add milk, margarine or butter, salt and pepper.
Heat over low heat until hot.

title: grape jelly
directions: Wash off grapes.
Pick off grapes and put in a pan. Cook without water until done.
The way you know when grapes are done, the inside will come out of the hull (skin).
Strain and let the juice set. Add 2 cups of juice with every 2 cups juice and add 3 cups sugar. Stir and put on stove.
Cook until it comes to a rolling boil. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour in glass jars and seal.
Let set until jelly becomes jelly.

title: breakfast casserole(easy and quick)
directions: Tear up bread and place pieces in greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 3-inch).
Brown and drain sausage in skillet.
Drain off fat. Spoon meat over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cheese will rise to top during baking.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tender brisket
directions: You also need a cooking bag.

title: chowder parmesan
directions: Add all of this to 2 cups boiling water; simmer until tender.

title: hot tamales
directions: Soak corn shucks in hot water for about an hour or more; the longer, the better.
Boil the meat until tender; save the liquid broth.
Chop the meat real good.
On the stove, put a frying pan with a little Crisco.
Put the chopped pork in and brown a little. Add garlic salt, cumin and a small amount of chili powder.
Pour a little broth in and stir and cook for 10 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute leeks and parsley in a saucepan with butter.
In a large saucepan, place potatoes, sauteed leeks and parsley and add enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Add salt.
Reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are cooked.
Put entire mixture through a sieve or puree in an electric blender.
Return to a saucepan and add milk.
Beat in egg yolks.
Serve with a teaspoon of butter and croutons in each bowl.

title: candy nuts
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, milk and water.
Cook on slow heat until it forms a soft ball. Pour out on waxed paper and separate.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in square metal pan sprayed with Pam.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400° (uncovered) or until done.
Serve over egg noodles.
Garnish with sliced lemons, if desired.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: sloppy joe pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn, water (optional) and seasoning mix.
Heat mixture until hot and bubbly; reduce heat and simmer while preparing crust.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits; flatten slightly.
Dip each in milk; dip in cornmeal.
Arrange 7 biscuits around sides and 3 in the bottom of 9-inch pie pan; press biscuits to form crust.
Sprinkle crust with 1/2 cup of the cheese. Spoon hot meat mixture over cheese; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is deep golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rich and thick milk shake
directions: Pour milk into electric blender container.
Add pudding mix, ice cream and ice.
Cover and blend at high speed for 1 minute. Serve at once.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat; stir in sugar, milk, vanilla and mace.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Excellent over pound cake, sponge cake, bread pudding or ice cream.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: chicken old mill
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in baking pan.
Heat soup, mayonnaise, milk and sherry.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Serve over rice. Serves 6 to 8.

title: shipwreck
directions: Brown meat; then layer everything in a greased casserole in order given.
Bake at 275° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: marble squares
directions: Blend the butter, vanilla, water and sugars.
Beat in egg.
Mix in flour mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped nuts, if desired.

title: creamy waldorf salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and juice in a small bowl; stir well and set mixture aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add cream cheese mixture to apple mixture; toss gently.
Cover and chill.
Toss again before serving.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl. Serves 6 to 8.

title: clam spaghetti
directions: Heat sauce to boiling and add drained clams to sauce; cook for a few minutes for flavor.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: easy stuffed potato
directions: Split potatoes and wrap in tinfoil. Bake until done. Scoop out inside and mix with butter, cheese and bacon bits. Replace in shell and sprinkle with cheese. Broil until cheese melts.

title: picadillo tarts
directions: Cook ground chuck beef and onion in a skillet until meat is browned; drain well.
Stir in almonds and the next 6 ingredients. Place 1 sheet of phyllo on a damp towel (keep remaining phyllo covered).
Lightly brush phyllo with melted butter.
Top with another sheet and brush again with melted butter.
Fold in half, placing long edges together to make a 17 x 6-inch rectangle.
Cut into 10 equal portions using a sharp knife.
Repeat procedure with remaining phyllo.
Press each portion of phyllo into a lightly greased miniature muffin cup, forming a shell.
Spoon about 1 teaspoon of the beef mixture into each shell.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate until ready to bake.
Remove plastic wrap.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, or until golden brown.
Gently remove from pan; serve warm or at room temperature.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes 50 appetizers.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and mix all ingredients. Roll into balls and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute onion in butter in a large saucepan.
Add soup, milk and green chiles and blend well on top of stove or in microwave at Medium.
Roll tortillas with chicken and 1/2 the cheese and set side by side in casserole.
Pour sauce over top.
Work down in between.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or microwave 20 minutes on High.
Serves 8.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together well.
Put in unbaked 9-inch pie shell and cut margarine up and place all over top.
Cover with strips.
Bake in 425° oven.
Check in 20 minutes and bake until done (heat may need to be lowered after 20 minutes).

title: potato dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Combine with potatoes, bread crumbs, eggs, parsley and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes in covered dish.

title: luscious flan(pleases eye as well as palate)
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar in a heavy saucepan; put over medium heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and syrup is light golden brown.
Pour syrup into six 6-ounce custard cups.
Let cool.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Top should be golden.
Cool on a rack and cut into squares.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts, set aside.
Boil mixed vegetables and drain.
In a bowl mix vegetables, soups and deboned chicken with 1 cup of reserved chicken broth.
Pour in casserole dish.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir. Combine peaches and remaining 1 cup sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Yield: Approximately 10 servings.

title: rufus's vegetable stew
directions: Cook meat in large saucepan until tender and add the vegetables and cook until done.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease 15 x 10-inch pan.
Line with wax paper and grease. Beat eggs 5 minutes.
Add gradually sugar, then pumpkin.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Pour into pan; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Take it out of the oven and turn over onto a towel with 10x sugar sprinkled on it.
Roll long ways; let cool 1 1/2 hours.
Roll out and spread with filling (recipe follows).
May be frozen or refrigerated.

title: cream cheese pecan frosting
directions: Mix powdered sugar, softened cream cheese, softened margarine, salt and milk until smooth.
Add pecans and coconut.
Spread over cake layers.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Mix lime
and
water
together and pour over cucumbers; let stand 24 hours.
Add enough water to cover pickles.
Wash, drain and put in fresh, cool water for 3 hours; drain.
Simmer alum, 1 cup
vinegar,
red
color
and
enough
water to cover cucumbers; simmer 2
hours,
then drain.
Make syrup of 3 cups vinegar, sugar,
red
hots,
cups
water, salt and cinnamon sticks; boil for 5 minutes,
then
pour
over cukes.
Pour off syrup for 4 mornings;
bring
to boil and pour over cucumbers. On fourth morning, pack in jars.
Cover with boiling syrup and seal.

title: chewy coconut macaroons
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat egg whites until soft mounds form. Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in 1 cup sugar and remaining ingredients carefully, half at a time, until thoroughly blended.

title: garlic pasta chicken
directions: In large skillet, generously cover bottom with olive oil. Saute garlic salt and fresh garlic.
Add chopped chicken.
Cook, stirring, 15 minutes.
Add chopped red pepper.
Stir and cook 8 to 10 minutes.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix together tapioca pudding, vanilla pudding, orange extract and the 3 cups of water.
Let stand for 10 minutes so tapioca gets soft.
Cook until thick.
Boil for 1 minute.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and oranges.
Stir until blended good. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: marinated carrots
directions: In a large bowl, combine ingredients.
Blend together and chill (can be made ahead).

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Spread graham crackers in cookie pan.
Mix margarine, brown sugar and pecans in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over crackers.
Cook on broil 2 to 3 minutes.
Topping will look bubbly.

title: speedy taco bake
directions: Cook beef and onion until done. Spoon into baking dish.
Stir in taco mix, tomato sauce and corn.
Sprinkle on cheese.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift two times.
Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Begin with flour and end with flour.
Add flavoring.
Beat at slow speed. Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Start in cold oven.
This does not use baking powder.
May use 2 teaspoons vanilla instead of almond.

title: spanish spaghetti
directions: Heat oil; add onions and green peppers.
Cook until soft.
Add ground beef, salt, black pepper and chili pepper.
Cook until browned.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste and 4 cups tomatoes and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Cook together 15 minutes on medium heat.
Break spaghetti into pieces and cook according to directions on package. Do not overcook.
Drain and add to sauce mix and put into casserole.
Put into oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: betty bowen's noodles and cabbage
directions: Fry cabbage "slowly" in 1 stick butter (should take about 1 hour on low). Be careful not to burn, light brown is okay.
While cabbage is cooking, make noodles.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in a skillet.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the vegetables and pour soup over.
Remove chops from pan, remove fat from skillet and add water to rinse and scrape particles from bottom of skillet.
Pour this over vegetables.
Sprinkle with thyme.
Place chops on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
If chops get too brown during cooking, cover with glass lid or foil.

title: chili dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add chili and mix well.
Heat in microwave or on stove.
Serve with corn chips.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender; drain.
Combine noodles, drained tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Bake at 425° about 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift remaining ingredients together and blend into mixture.
Form into rolls; wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Combine kraut, onion and parsley; toss until well mixed. Spread dressing on each slice of bread.
Top 8 slices of bread with corned beef, cheese and kraut mixture; top with remaining bread.
Lightly butter both sides of sandwiches.
Grill slowly until cheese melts and bread browns.

title: chicken soup with meatballs
directions: Bring chicken broth and water to boil.
Add pasta and cook 5 minutes.
Add spinach and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Mix the ground meat, cheese and garlic and drop from teaspoon into soup.
Simmer 7 minutes until no longer pink inside.
Stir in 3 cups of vegetables and simmer until done (onion, carrots, celery, zucchini).

title: banana split
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients 5 minutes in mixer.
Spread over crumbs made of graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Mix and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Cut 5 bananas in 1/2 pieces.
Layer in pan.
Next, layer pineapple.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Garnish with coconut, maraschino cherries and chopped nuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna salad mold
directions: Heat soup and water to boiling point.
Add Jell-O.
When mixture is partly set, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into molds. Chill until set.
Makes 8 molds.

title: old-fashioned creamed corn
directions: Remove husks and silks from corn.
Rinse corn and pat dry.
Cut corn from cobs (about 3 cups); to cut corn from cob:
with very sharp knife, first cut, just barely take the top of the kernels, second cut, take about half-way of kernels and third cut, use blade of knife and scrape down to cob.
This gets the milk out of corn. Place butter in 2-quart casserole; microwave at High for 55 seconds, until butter melts.
Add corn, 1/4 cup water and sugar, stirring well.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Cook on High 8 to 9 minutes or until corn is tender, stirring after 4 minutes. Shake 1/2 cup water, salt, pepper and flour in pan until flour is blended smooth.
Stir into corn, mixing well.
Cook on High 3 minutes or until mixture slightly thickens.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set till dry onions are limp and no longer crunchy. Use for fish topping or anything else you like to use tartar sauce on.

title: picadio
directions: Brown and drain beef. Add onion, tomatoes, garlic, vinegar, oil, cinnamon, cloves, salt, raisins with stock and green olives. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: slush . . . . slush
directions: Mix and put in freezer.

title: corn pone
directions: Blend sugar and Crisco.
Add egg which was beaten slightly to sugar and Crisco.
Add sour milk.
Sift together soda, cornmeal, flour and salt.
Stir into mixture.
Pour into a greased pan and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple spoon bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs then cream again.
Add bread and pineapple including juice from can.
Pour into buttered dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Halve eggplant lengthwise.
Hollow out center.
Cook sausage; drain.
In a large bowl, mix sausage, eggplant centers, tomatoes, squash, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stuff into eggplant shells.
Spoon 4 tablespoons of tomato sauce over each.
Mix bread crumbs, oregano, egg and remaining tomato sauce.
Spoon over eggplant.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 6.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart pan or slow cooker. Simmer for 45 minutes.
Add more milk, if needed.
Add salt to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.
