title: coconut meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy, white and double in volume in a medium bowl.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating all the time until meringue stands in firm peaks.
Fold in vanilla and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon, 2 inches apart, on greased and floured large sheets.
Bake in very slow oven (250°) for 35 minutes or until lightly golden.
Remove from sheet to wire racks.
Let stand to cool completely.

title: williamsburg salad(serves 12)
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water.
Add sugar, pineapple juice, vinegar, salt and green coloring.
Chill until slightly thickened, then add pecan meats, India relish, pineapple and olives.
Pour into molds or a flat serving dish which has been rubbed with oil. Chill until firm and serve.
Unusual!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, soda, baking powder,
cinnamon and Wesson oil.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in a tube cake pan for 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine
mushroom
soup
and
1 cup of broth and put in bottom of	pan.
Add
half
of
stuffing
on top of soup.	Add chicken on	top of stuffing.
Put chicken soup with other cup of
broth on chicken.
Add the remaining stuffing on top.
You can
use frozen broccoli, if desired, on top of chicken.
Bake with aluminum foil on pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, cloves and baking powder.
Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix light, but well.
Add dry ingredients.
Divide into 3 loaf pans, greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together.
Drain; mash well.
Drain again.
Melt margarine in 9-inch baking dish.
Pour melted margarine into squash.
Mix all ingredients well except cracker crumbs.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until firm and top is brown.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, peppers and onions in food chopper or processor. Add all the ingredients to the vinegar and sugar.
Boil 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the chocolate bits and beat for 3 minutes.
Fold in bits and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325°.
After 1 hour check with cake tester.
Bake until batter does not stick to tester.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: o'charley's loaded potato soup
directions: Bring water to a boil in large pot. Add potatoes to water along with chicken stock base, salt and pepper. Cook 12 minutes or until potatoes are about half-done. Add Cheddar cheese soup and simmer 10 minutes. Melt butter or margarine in a heavy saucepan. Add flour and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 3 to 4 minutes. Do not brown. Whisk flour mixture into the potato mixture and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer an additional 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in half and half and heat to serving temperature. Do not boil. Serve with chives, bacon bits and parsley.

title: fran's easy cobbler
directions: Defrost pie crust. Butter 1 large baking pan.
Line bottom and sides of pan with two of the pie crusts.
Pour peaches into bowl. Mix all ingredients.
Squash peaches and mix until flour is mixed well.
Pour into pan and cut the two crusts you have left into strips. Cover top and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: highland griddle scones
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into mixing bowl.
Cut in Crisco thoroughly, until particles are fine. Break egg into measuring cup; add enough milk to measure 3/4 cup. Blend together.
Add all at once to flour mixture; stir just until moist.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add spices and simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Then add tomatoes, V-8 and rice.
Cook until rice is done.
You may add more V-8, if desired.

title: cashew drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together alternately with sour cream.
Blend well.
Fold in nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Cool and top with golden butter glaze.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook 7-Up,
sugar and cornstarch until thick and clear. Cool, then pour over strawberries.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all together; put in crock-pot.
Cook for 2 or 3 hours. Great to take for carry-ins.

title: decorating dough
directions: Mix flour and salt in a large bowl.
Slowly add water.
Form ball.
Knead dough for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add flour (if sticky) and water (if stiff).
May refrigerate dough up to 5 days.
Make ornaments, crafts, etc.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add chicken, carrots, bean sprouts, corn and seasonings.
Cook on simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Wrap 2 tablespoonfuls of mixture in each egg roll skin and seal edges.
Place in deep fryer until browned.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: Melt margarine and mix with other ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: crab bisque
directions: Drain crabmeat, and remove any bits of shell.
Set aside.

title: french omelet
directions: Separate yolks from whites.
Beat whites until light; add salt and beat until stiff and dry.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; add milk and pepper.
Fold egg whites and baking powder into the yolks.
Melt butter in frying pan; pour in egg mixture and heat slowly until omelet has set.
Put in a 325° oven for 30 minutes, or until omelet browns on top.
Serve immediately with Spanish sauce.
Yield:
5 servings.

title: venison roast
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add meat.
Spoon remaining mixture over roast. Combine water and wine.
Pour over roast.
Cover and marinate for 2 days in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender, basting occasionally with pan drippings.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In pan bring 1 cup pineapple juice to boil.
Take off heat and add Jell-O.
Mix real good, then add Sprite.
Mix pineapple, cranberries and pecans.
Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Chill until set.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Stew peaches with 2 or 3 cloves.
Simmer other ingredients 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour over peaches.
Store in refrigerator.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls and press in jelly roll pan, pressing seams together.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch mix; spread on cooled crescent crust.
Add vegetables, making sure you press them into the cream cheese mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sloppy jewels
directions: Cook and drain beef.
Saute onions, pepper and garlic for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve on rolls.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, cornstarch and a pinch of salt in a heavy saucepan. Add egg yolk and mix well.
Heat coffee cream to near boil. Add to egg mixture and mix well.
Place over medium heat and stir until thick.
Slowly add vinegar, beating constantly. Serve warm over meat.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except shrimp, rice, flour and water.
Cook until pepper and celery are tender.
Add flour, shrimp and last of all water.
Cook over low heat until shrimp are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: *little jewels salad
directions: Mix lime jello with 1 cup of hot water and 1/2 cup of cold water.
Put into pan to set.
Do the same with the cherry and orange jellos.
Chill in the refrigerator.
Mix sugar, pineapple juice and 1/4 cup water in saucepan; let come to a boil.
Mix with lemon jello.
Let set on counter until it jells.
Mix the Dream Whip and milk.
When thoroughly whipped, add lemon jello mixture. Cut lime, cherry and orange jellos into small cubes.
Fold into whipped mixture and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Use broth from chicken.
Throw in chicken and other ingredients.
Cook until thick.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Season to taste.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Pour hot water over Jell-O; add pineapple juice and while still warm.
Add marshmallows and cheese.
When cool, add pineapple and nuts.
When it begins to thicken and congeal, fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: jessie's front flip fudge
directions: Prepare pan by buttering bottom and sides of 9-inch square pan.
Dice marshmallows.
Set aside.
Mix evaporated milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Heat mixture over low heat until it just boils, then cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly with wooden spoon.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows melt.
Pour in pan. Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt
oleo in soup pot.
Add onion, carrots and celery. Saute until
soft.
Add
flour
and
cornstarch.	Cook
until bubbly. Add broth and milk and make a smooth sauce.
Add soda and cheese. Garnish with parsley before serving.

title: stir crazy cake
directions: Put flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, cocoa, soda and salt into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch metal baking pan.
Stir with a fork to mix.
Form 3 wells in the flour mixture. Pour oil into one well, vinegar in the second and vanilla in the third.
Pour cold coffee over all ingredients and stir with fork until well mixed.
Do not beat.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pixie pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco, butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring; beat well.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add chocolate and butterscotch chips; set aside.
Mix flour, soda, salt, cocoa and sugar.
Add oil, vanilla and water.
Beat together until smooth.

title: chocolate cake and icing
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring butter, water, shortening and cocoa to boil.
Pour over flour mixture and mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Drain and rinse in cold water.
Add tuna, peas, onions, cheese and salt to taste.
Blend in enough mayo to make creamy.

title: pizza cups
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add ground beef.
Cook until brown, stirring until crumbly.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings; mix well.
Simmer for 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through.

title: salmon salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Chop eggs.
Mix mayonnaise and Ranch dressing. Mix all ingredients with macaroni.
Chill in refrigerator or serve warm.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: chicken-rice twosome
directions: Coat chicken with flour, onion powder, paprika and pepper.
In skillet, brown chicken in hot margarine.
In a small saucepan, heat water and bouillon cubes until dissolved.
Stir in sherry.
In bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine water mixture, rice, mushrooms, celery and onion.
Place chicken on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed and chicken is tender.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken and stuffing scallop
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with layer of chicken.
In large saucepan melt butter.
Blend flour and seasonings.
Add cool broth.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Stir small amount of mixture into eggs.
Return to hot mix.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes to set. Cut in squares to serve with pimento mushroom sauce.
Serves 12.

title: fluffy pink salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: calico bean pot
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock pot and cook on high for at least 4-6 hours.

title: pineapple coconut pie(2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs until light and fluffy. Combine dry ingredients, then add alternately with milk, beating well.
Beat in bananas and vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured pan (9 x 13 x 2-inches).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat. Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Simmer 5 minutes. Unroll dough.
Press onto bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cover crust with meat mixture and cheese.
Continue baking until cheese begins to melt.
Top with remaining ingredients. Serve with sour cream, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lib's crab appetizer
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of a platter.
Cover with the chopped onions.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce over the onions. Mix ketchup, horseradish and Tabasco and spoon over the layered ingredients.
Top with the crab.
Sprinkle a little lemon juice over crab.
Finish off with chopped parsley.
Serve with crackers. Delicious!!

title: mini blintzes
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar and yolks together.
Cut crusts from the bread and roll
the bread thin.
Spread the slices with the cream cheese mixture.
Roll up bread.
Dip each in melted oleo, then roll in the cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake for 10 - 15 minutes at 400 degrees.
Cut in half.
Serve plain or with sour cream.
You can freeze these to cook later.

title: frozen champagne salad
directions: Soften and blend cream cheese with sugar.
Mix together drained pineapple, strawberries with juice, bananas, nuts and whipped topping.
Combine 2 mixtures.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: rhubarb-cherry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Add filling.
Add top crust.
Flute edges.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Shred cooked chicken breasts in a baking dish.
Saute onions and celery.
Mix celery soup, chicken soup, celery and onions. Pour on top of chicken.
Mix Stove Top stuffing according to package directions.
Top chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add vanilla, lemon juice and condensed milk and mix.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill 2 hours.

title: sweet-treat fried ice cream
directions: With scoop, form 6 ice cream balls.
Place on wax paper-covered tray; cover and freeze several hours or until very firm.

title: marsha's casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, sugar and mushroom soup.
Cook for 10 minutes on medium.
Pour in casserole dish cooked noodles and sauce.
Then put cheese all in the casserole.
Cut in 1-inch strips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: olive macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients and chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, oranges and cherries.
In a large bowl, mix fruit cocktail, oranges and cherries.
Add sour cream, chopped walnuts, marshmallows and coconut.
Mix until all is blended. Place in another dish.
Cool in refrigerator for 2 hours and serve.

title: chile cheese casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add salt and pepper to taste and a pinch of garlic. Open chilies and clean seeds from them.
Spread in the bottom of well buttered 8 x 8-inch Pyrex baking dish, alternating cheese and chilies in layers.
Pour eggs over and bake 40 minutes at 350°. Cut into one-inch squares or smaller.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple well. Add remaining ingredients. Mix. Refrigerate.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips in microwave; stir.
Mix in all of peanut butter.
Mix in all of Crispix.
Make sure Crispix is covered with first mixture.
Pour enough powdered sugar into a bag; add cereal. Shake well.
Place in a covered container.

title: fried chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Combine egg and milk.
Dip chicken in egg mixture.
Drop into paper bag with flour.
Shake to coat.
Place in hot oil in heavy deep skillet. Cover.
Fry at 350° to 400° until brown.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix ground beef, rice and onion together.
Stuff it inside peppers.
Pour jar of spaghetti sauce in pan.
Add 1/2 jar of water.
Add peppers and cook at medium heat for 2 to 3 hours.

title: easy pineapple cake frosting
directions: Mix the pineapple with juice into the dry pudding mix.
Stir until pudding mix dissolves.
Stir in nondairy topping.
Spread between and on the outside of your cake layers.
Refrigerate cake after icing.
Yields enough to frost 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan cake or 2 layers.
Use white or yellow cake mix.

title: b~b~q sauce
directions: Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 1 qt.

title: vegetable shira-ae
directions: Place tofu on paper towel, changing paper towel until most of water has drained out.
Put tofu in bowl and mash with fork or potato masher.
Grind roasted sesame seed and add with rest of ingredients to tofu.
Mix well.
Use as dressing on boiled vegetables.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Spray saucepan and cooking pan.
Melt margarine over low heat in large saucepan.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal; stir until coated.
Use buttered spatula to press mixture into baking sheet.
Remove from sheet and add decorations (decorations optional).

title: no knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Measure sugar, salt and shortening; add 1 1/2 cups warm water in a large bowl.
Beat in yeast and eggs.
Add 2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough and mix well.
Place in a greased bowl; cover and let rise until doubled (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down, cover tightly and refrigerate.
(Dough keeps 3 to 4 days.) Remove dough from refrigerator.
Shape rolls.
Let rise until doubled (about 45 minutes).
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush top with butter.
Makes 24 servings.

title: 10 day cole slaw
directions: Boil sugar, oil, salt, dried mustard and celery seed for 5 minutes.
Pour over cabbage, onions and green pepper.
Let cool; mix and refrigerate.
This will keep at least 10
days.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and leave juice in meat.
Add diced onion and pepper.
Let simmer 5 to 10 minutes, then add remaining ingredients, preferably tomatoes first.
Also, add 1 cup of water. Cook for about 2 hours and remove lid for the last 45 minutes for thicker chili.

title: blueberry oatmeal muffins
directions: Fold together blueberries and 2 tablespoons flour.
Set aside. Mix remaining ingredients and add floured blueberries.
Put into muffin cups (may use liners and put 1/2 cup mixture into each). Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes
and onion in enough water to cover, with salt and pepper, until
almost done. Add milk and butter. Cook until done, stirring
often. Can be thickened with cornstarch, if desired.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown, stirring once.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients but stuffing and nuts.
Empty into a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with stuffing and nuts. You may drizzle top with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: very good and easy zucchini cheese quiche
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add cheese, zucchini, Bisquick and margarine.
Mix thoroughly.
Mix soda, baking powder and milk and pour into zucchini mixture.
Mix well and pour into buttered, 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: maple nut chiffon cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Make a well and add Wesson oil, egg yolks, water and maple flavoring. Beat until smooth with electric mixer using medium speed for one minute.
In a large bowl, add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat with electric mixer until whites form very stiff peaks on high speed for 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not underbeat.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over beaten egg whites, gently folding with rubber spatula, just until blended.
Add nuts.
Do not stir.
Pour into ungreased 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Bake 55 minutes at 325°, then increase to 350° for 10 to 15 minutes longer or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Turn pan upside-down and cool.
Let hang until cold.
Remove and frost with the following.

title: punch bowl chocolate mousse cake
directions: Punch holes in cake and pour Amaretto over; let set.
Layer: Crumbled cake, mousse, whipped cream and Heath bars.
Make several layers with all ingredients.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except Coca-Cola and marshmallows in large bowl; blend at low speed.
Beat one minute at medium speed; add Coca-Cola and blend well by hand.
Stir in marshmallows.
Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In a large frypan, flour beef with 1/2 cup flour; add onions and oil and brown.
Stir in paprika, marjoram, pepper, green pepper, garlic, tomatoes and 1 cup of water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook approximately 90 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet over low heat.
Add chopped onion and saute until onion is transparent.
Stir in whipping cream. Mix well.
Now, stir in Parmesan cheese.
When this is mixed well, add cooked peas.
Continue to cook over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over fettucini noodles.
You can use broccoli, shrimp, etc. instead of peas.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix the flour, buttermilk and oil together in a bowl until mixture becomes a dough.
Sprinkle occasionally with flour as you knead this a few times.
In another bowl, mix the sugar and sweet potatoes together.
Press dough in the center and add sweet potatoes to this.
Begin kneading the dough until well mixed. Roll or pat out to desired thickness.
Cut biscuits.
Bake in oven oven at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix the drained fruits and mix all ingredients together.
Garnish, if desired, with halved cherries.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pepparkokar(swedish christmas cookies)
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and molasses together in mixer.
Add flour, soda and spices.
Chill dough in refrigerator; roll thin and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Dough may also be shaped into "logs", frozen and sliced from ends; not as pretty, but much easier!)

title: chocolate brittal chip cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add butter, vanilla and eggs. Mix again.
While mixing, add chocolate chips and Bit-o-Brittal. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare chicken and let cool.
Cook stuffing as directed on box.
Do not cook peas or preheat gravy.
Take glass baking dish and put either 1 box stuffing or a half of box to cover bottom. Layer chicken, then peas and stuffing.
Pour gravy on top and heat until hot or warm.
Serves 8.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, add coconut. Mix until coconut is coated with butter; add milk, eggs and sugar.
Mix well.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: non-alcoholic punch
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Float orange slices on top. Add cherries.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, sugar and oleo until crumbly and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: delicious orange cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, vanilla and orange rind.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together well; form into loaf and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Combine Jell-o, pineapple (juice included), 1 cup water and 2 Tbsp. sugar in saucepan. Dissolve Jell-o and cook until mixture comes to a boil. Set aside to cool completely.

title: herb roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut potatoes in slices like French fries and place in large bowl with other ingredients.
Toss well and place on a nonstick baking sheet and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: guyanese garlic pork(traditional christmas breakfast dish)
directions: You will also need 2 large airtight glass jars (Mason jars ideal).

title: quick cinnamon twist
directions: Pull each biscuit out to about 6-inches long.
Dip in melted butter and roll in mixture of nuts, cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tomatoes yemistess(greece)
directions: Cook meat, butter and onion until browned in saucepan or electric skillet.
Add parsley, almonds, cinnamon, salt and sugar. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add rice.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes. Hollow out tomatoes, reserving pulp and juice.
Fill with rice mixture.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine salmon, cracker crumbs, egg, onion, parsley and pepper.
Blend well.
Shape into patties.
Fry over medium heat.

title: yummy pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add fruit (drained) and fold in topping. Put in icebox until set, about 30 minutes.

title: winter soup
directions: Simmer ham and sausage in 3 1/2 quarts of water.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until tender.
Remove ham and sausage and cut up. Return to water.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add egg and continue beating the egg.
Add persimmon pulp.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch square pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and flavorings.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Do this sifting 3 more times.
Blend both mixtures together.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll dough out on floured cloth or board and cut in desired shapes.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 400° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Watch carefully to avoid burning.
Yields 10 dozen round cookies 3 inches in diameter.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Blend sugar and cream cheese.
Mix all other ingredients with sugar and cream cheese.
Add the Cool Whip. Blend again. Spread all in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Will keep for a long time. Thaw 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Use either a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or a jelly roll pan/cookie sheet approximately 1 inch deep.
Spray bottom of pan with Pam before you begin to layer sheets of filo dough.
You will layer 10 to 12 sheets of filo dough, making sure you brush butter on top of each new sheet.
Keep a damp cloth over the filo dough so it does not dry out.
After you have layered your last sheet of dough, spread your cheese/spinach mixture.
Now begin laying the next 10 to 12 sheets of filo dough, again brushing butter on top of each sheet.
Be sure to cut off excess dough and score or cut into squares before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cheese/spinach mixture:
Mix together the eggs, drained spinach, cheese, salt, pepper, dill, garlic and onion.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar.
Beat in egg.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 1 rounded teaspoonful of mixture in each cupcake paper.
Top with cake batter.
Bake as directed on cake box.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to package directions. Combine Kool-Aid and pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and mix well.

title: two minute chocolate fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla and nuts in large glass bowl.
Microwave for 2 minutes on High power.
Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased dish and chill.

title: icebox delite
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cream together eggs, margarine and sugars; sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix into cream mixture.
Form into rolls (logs).
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
Slice and bake in a moderate oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Bake on lightly greased pan.

title: whoopie pie cake
directions: Beat several minutes and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in middle of oven.
Grease, flour and line 9 1/2 x 13-inch cake pan with wax paper.
After it is baked and cooled, lift cake out of pan onto oblong serving tray.
Cut lengthwise through the middle. Lift carefully with both hands under top part.
Put icing in the middle and replace the top.

title: chinese jello salad
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 cup. Add to gelatin; add soy sauce and lemon juice. Stir until ice is melted and gelatin is slightly thickened. Remove any unmelted ice. Add remaining ingredients and spoon into individual dishes or a bowl. Chill until set, at least 30 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 cups or 5 servings. Contains 25 calories per serving.

title: parmesan sauce
directions: Combine milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Add cheese, seasonings and mushrooms; stir well.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and blend well.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Combine remaining ingredients in medium saucepan and mix well.
Add meatballs, stirring lightly to coat with sauce. Simmer about one hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes 32 to 36 meatballs.

title: tomato-sherried eggs
directions: Combine
first
ingredients
with 1/2 teaspoon salt. Place in
a
buttered
x 6 x 1 1/2-inch casserole.
Form 8 wells in tomato mixture.
Crack 1 egg into each well. Sprinkle with cheese and
remaining
1/4 teaspoon salt. Bake in a preheated oven
until eggs are set, about 10 to 15 minutes. Serve
with cooked
bacon
or sausage and toast or biscuits, if desired. Serves 4 to 8.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add zucchini and then sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins if desired.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
with nuts and raisins, 2 regular or 6 small loaves.
Without nuts and raisins, 2 medium or 3 small loaves.

title: vidalia onion casserole(serves 6)
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, broth and evaporated milk.
Stir constantly until mixture begins to thicken and is smooth.
Stir cheese into sauce.
Drain onions and add to sauce with salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Fry beef and garlic gently and keep juice.
Also add mushrooms and big onions.
Mix ingredients and place in casserole.
